<font color="#ffff00">四签名</font>

5
00:02:44,585 --> 00:02:45,911
有个年轻漂亮的女人
There's a very pretty young woman

6
00:02:45,948 --> 00:02:47,603
走过街来
crossing the street

7
00:02:48,225 --> 00:02:51,555
我想她可能要到这
and I think she may be coming here.

8
00:02:51,902 --> 00:02:54,387
顺便说一句 我大概看了一下
Incidentally, I have glanced over

9
00:02:54,497 --> 00:02:55,622
你对我工作的最新记录
your latest account of my work.

10
00:02:55,660 --> 00:02:56,895
怎么了
Oh yes.

11
00:02:57,930 --> 00:03:01,590
坦白的讲 我并不赞同
Honestly I cannot congratulate you upon it.

12
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:07,654
侦探学是一门非常精确的科学
Detection is, or ought to be, an exact science.

13
00:03:08,510 --> 00:03:11,251
应是观察后的推理
Observation deduction

14
00:03:11,367 --> 00:03:12,875
要有冷静非感性的大脑研究它
a cold and unemotional subject.

15
00:03:13,231 --> 00:03:15,484
你试图给它加上浪漫的色彩
You have attempted to tinge it with romanticism,

16
00:03:15,521 --> 00:03:17,202
这就像把爱情故事
which has much the same effect

17
00:03:17,315 --> 00:03:18,867
或是一场私奔
as if you worked a love-story or an

18
00:03:18,984 --> 00:03:22,270
变成欧几里德的第五个几何命题一样
elopement into the fifth proposition of Euclid.

19
00:03:22,308 --> 00:03:23,964
一点都不搭调
Who can match that?

20
00:03:25,666 --> 00:03:29,022
有位年轻的女士要见你 福尔摩斯先生
There's a young lady to see you Mr. Holmes.

21
00:03:31,715 --> 00:03:32,756
是Mary Morstan
It's Mary Morstan.

22
00:03:32,794 --> 00:03:35,216
这名字我一点都没印象
I have no recollection of the name.

23
00:03:38,429 --> 00:03:40,900
别走 医生 我可能需要你
Don't go Doctor, I may need you.

24
00:03:41,344 --> 00:03:43,878
我没猜错
I was right.

25
00:03:47,090 --> 00:03:48,923
谢谢
Thank you.

26
00:03:48,961 --> 00:03:49,889
Morstan女士
Miss Morstan.

27
00:03:49,926 --> 00:03:52,008
下午好
Good afternoon.

28
00:03:57,291 --> 00:03:58,749
我今天来找你 福尔摩斯先生
I have come to you Mr. Holmes

29
00:03:58,786 --> 00:04:01,176
是因为你曾为我的雇主
because you once enabled my employer,

30
00:04:01,213 --> 00:04:02,256
Cecil Forrester夫人
Mrs. Cecil Forrester,

31
00:04:02,294 --> 00:04:05,683
解决了一次小型家庭纠纷
to unravel a minor domestic complication.

32
00:04:06,055 --> 00:04:07,607
她对你的善意和智慧
She was much impressed

33
00:04:07,646 --> 00:04:09,770
印象深刻
with your kindness and skill.

34
00:04:10,865 --> 00:04:11,911
谢谢
Thank you.

35
00:04:24,968 --> 00:04:27,770
我想象不出 有什么比我现在的处境
I can hardly imagine anything more strange,

36
00:04:27,807 --> 00:04:30,869
更加...奇怪
more utterly inexplicable,

37
00:04:30,907 --> 00:04:33,338
或是更令人费解的了
than the situation in which I find myself.

38
00:04:33,376 --> 00:04:35,447
说说案情吧
State your case.

39
00:04:35,484 --> 00:04:37,458
抱歉 失陪了
You will, I am sure, excuse me.

40
00:04:37,497 --> 00:04:40,147
你的朋友再坐会吧
If your friend would be good enough to remain,

41
00:04:41,218 --> 00:04:44,782
也许还需要他的帮助
he might be of inestimable service to me.

42
00:04:44,819 --> 00:04:46,309
好吧
Of course.

43
00:04:56,585 --> 00:04:58,994
简单的说...
Briefly the facts are these.

44
00:05:01,076 --> 00:05:04,426
我父亲是一名派驻到印度的军官
My father was an officer in an Indian regiment.

45
00:05:04,715 --> 00:05:08,445
我母亲在我还很小的时候就去世了
My mother died when I was still quite a child

46
00:05:09,113 --> 00:05:12,216
他不得不把我送回国内
and he was forced to send me home,

47
00:05:12,253 --> 00:05:15,231
虽然国内已没有亲戚在了
despite the fact that I had no relatives here.

48
00:05:15,712 --> 00:05:17,544
我被安排在爱丁堡
I was placed in a

49
00:05:17,582 --> 00:05:18,953
一个舒适的寄宿学校读书
comfortable boarding establishment

50
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:20,085
我一直在那儿
at Edinburgh, and I remained there

51
00:05:20,122 --> 00:05:22,419
呆到17岁才离开
until I was 1 7 years of age.

52
00:05:22,916 --> 00:05:26,599
就在那年 我父亲...
In that same year my father,

53
00:05:26,637 --> 00:05:29,052
那个团里资格最老的上尉
who was a senior captain of his regiment,

54
00:05:30,888 --> 00:05:35,680
请了一年的假回家
obtained 12 months' leave and returned home.

55
00:05:37,490 --> 00:05:39,073
他到达伦敦后 发电报给我说
He telegraphed to me from London to say

56
00:05:39,110 --> 00:05:41,359
他已平安到达
that he had arrived all safe

57
00:05:41,396 --> 00:05:43,384
让我马上到这来
and directed me to come down at once,

58
00:05:43,422 --> 00:05:46,467
给了我他居住的 Langham旅馆的地址
giving the Langham Hotel as his address.

59
00:05:47,021 --> 00:05:50,428
我记得他的电报里
His message, as I remember,

60
00:05:50,465 --> 00:05:53,128
充满慈爱
was full of love and kindness.

61
00:05:54,602 --> 00:05:55,553
一到伦敦
On reaching London

62
00:05:55,591 --> 00:05:58,031
我就直接去了Langham旅店
I drove straight to the Langham Hotel

63
00:05:58,068 --> 00:06:01,015
那儿的人告诉我说 确实有一位Morstan上尉住在这里
and was informed that Captain Morstan

64
00:06:01,053 --> 00:06:03,515
但是他已经出去两天了
was staying there,

65
00:06:03,553 --> 00:06:06,108
还没有回来
but that he had gone out the night before

66
00:06:04,237 --> 00:06:06,453
and had not returned.

67
00:06:06,146 --> 00:06:08,294
于是我等在那里
So I waited

68
00:06:10,340 --> 00:06:12,239
一整天
all day

69
00:06:12,929 --> 00:06:15,462
没有他的任何消息
without news of him.

70
00:06:17,847 --> 00:06:21,986
那天夜里
And that night,

71
00:06:22,278 --> 00:06:25,101
在旅馆经理的建议下
on the advice of the manager of the hotel,

72
00:06:26,991 --> 00:06:30,001
我找了警察
I communicated with the police,

73
00:06:32,841 --> 00:06:34,289
第二天又在各种报纸上
the next day we advertised

74
00:06:34,326 --> 00:06:36,792
登了寻人启事
in all the newspapers.

75
00:06:38,494 --> 00:06:41,332
可是一点结果都没有
Our inquiries led to no result

76
00:06:42,046 --> 00:06:44,913
从那天到现在
from that day to this

77
00:06:44,951 --> 00:06:46,245
没有任何关于
no word has ever been heard

78
00:06:46,282 --> 00:06:49,059
我不幸父亲的消息
of my unfortunate father.

79
00:06:57,630 --> 00:07:00,998
他这次回来本希望
He came home with his heart so full of hope

80
00:07:01,280 --> 00:07:03,140
找个安静的地方
to find some peace,

81
00:07:03,177 --> 00:07:05,508
享享清福
some comfort,

82
00:07:05,545 --> 00:07:07,767
没想到...
and instead

83
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:17,238
什么时候失踪的?
The date?

84
00:07:18,095 --> 00:07:19,187
12月3日
The 3rd of December

85
00:07:19,224 --> 00:07:21,997
十年前的今天
exactly 1 0 years ago.

86
00:07:24,307 --> 00:07:26,903
他的行李呢?
His luggage?

87
00:07:26,941 --> 00:07:29,013
在旅馆里
Remained at the hotel.

88
00:07:30,707 --> 00:07:33,307
从那些东西里找不到什么线索--
Oh there was nothing in it to suggest a clue --

89
00:07:33,344 --> 00:07:35,991
只有一些衣服 一些书
some clothes, some books,

90
00:07:36,029 --> 00:07:37,951
还有很多Andaman岛上
and a considerable number of curiosities

91
00:07:37,989 --> 00:07:39,918
带回来的古玩
from the Andaman Islands.

92
00:07:43,369 --> 00:07:44,990
我父亲是那儿的一个军官
My father had been one of the officers

93
00:07:45,027 --> 00:07:46,750
负责看守犯人
in charge of the convict-guard there.

94
00:07:46,787 --> 00:07:48,590
华生 这地方有点乱
Watson this place is a mess.

95
00:07:48,627 --> 00:07:50,100
他在伦敦有朋友吗?
Had he any friends in town?

96
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:52,890
我只知道一个人
Only one that we know of

97
00:07:52,928 --> 00:07:55,657
叫Sholto少校 和他在一个团里
Major Sholto, of his old regiment,

98
00:07:55,980 --> 00:07:58,506
驻孟买陆军第三十四团
the 34th Bombay Infantry.

99
00:07:59,462 --> 00:08:01,539
当然我联系过他
We communicated with the Major, of course,

100
00:08:01,575 --> 00:08:05,330
但是他似乎不知道
but he did not seem to know

101
00:08:05,368 --> 00:08:07,041
他的好兄弟来到英国
that his brother officer was in England.

102
00:08:07,078 --> 00:08:09,500
真是个奇怪的案子
It's a singular case.

103
00:08:15,585 --> 00:08:18,885
我还没和你说到
I have not yet communicated to you

104
00:08:19,196 --> 00:08:21,574
最奇怪的部分呢
the most singular part.

105
00:08:23,906 --> 00:08:25,018
4年后
4 years later

106
00:08:25,056 --> 00:08:27,195
泰晤士报上有一则广告
an advertisement had appeared in the Times

107
00:08:27,232 --> 00:08:29,600
征询我的地址
asking for the address of Miss Mary Morstan,

108
00:08:29,637 --> 00:08:31,934
声称要是回复他
and stating that it would be to her advantage

109
00:08:31,971 --> 00:08:33,628
就会会有好处
to come forward.

110
00:08:33,891 --> 00:08:35,960
广告没有署名
There was no name appended.

111
00:08:37,175 --> 00:08:38,432
那时侯
I had at the time

112
00:08:38,469 --> 00:08:41,282
我刚刚进入Cecil Forrester夫人家
just entered the family of Mrs. Cecil Forrester

113
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,961
做家庭教师
in the capacity of governess

114
00:08:42,998 --> 00:08:44,986
按照她的建议 我把地址登在了
and on her advice I published my address

115
00:08:45,023 --> 00:08:47,020
报纸的广告专栏上
in the advertisement column.

116
00:08:48,067 --> 00:08:50,880
就在同一天有个邮递员送给我
That same day there appeared through the post

117
00:08:50,918 --> 00:08:54,750
一个小纸盒
a small cardboard box addressed to me,

118
00:08:55,917 --> 00:08:57,909
盒里装的是
which I found to contain

119
00:08:57,947 --> 00:09:01,569
一个很大的上等珍珠
a very large and lustrous pearl.

120
00:09:01,703 --> 00:09:04,349
盒里没有一个字
No word of writing was enclosed.

121
00:09:04,386 --> 00:09:08,267
从那以后 每年的这天
And since then every year upon the same date

122
00:09:08,305 --> 00:09:10,678
都会有同样的盒子给我
there has always appeared a similar box,

123
00:09:10,715 --> 00:09:11,583
里面是同样的珍珠
containing a similar pearl,

124
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:14,042
没有任何寄珠人的线索
with no clue as to the sender.

125
00:09:14,565 --> 00:09:16,149
行家鉴定了之后
They have been pronounced by an expert

126
00:09:16,187 --> 00:09:17,692
说是很稀有的种类
to be of a rare variety

127
00:09:17,729 --> 00:09:20,641
很值钱
and of considerable value.

128
00:09:22,331 --> 00:09:23,283
你们请看
You can see for yourself

129
00:09:23,321 --> 00:09:25,603
的确很上等
that they are very handsome.

130
00:09:34,281 --> 00:09:36,644
你的案子很有趣
Your case is most interesting.

131
00:09:39,112 --> 00:09:41,521
还有别的情况吗?
Something else has occurred to you?

132
00:09:41,859 --> 00:09:44,238
是的 就在今天
Yes, and no later than today.

133
00:09:45,053 --> 00:09:47,811
这就是我来找你的原因
That is why I have come to you.

134
00:09:48,428 --> 00:09:52,562
今早我收到一封信
This letter arrived through the post this morning,

135
00:09:52,904 --> 00:09:55,642
您还是自己读读吧
which you will perhaps read for yourself.

136
00:09:56,117 --> 00:09:58,175
请把信封也给我
Envelope please.

137
00:10:00,476 --> 00:10:02,913
伦敦的邮戳 9月7日
London postmark, October 7th.

138
00:10:03,452 --> 00:10:05,943
角上有个男人的大拇指印
Man's thumb mark on corner

139
00:10:06,496 --> 00:10:08,488
可能是邮递员留下的
probably the postman.

140
00:10:10,457 --> 00:10:12,257
最好的纸
Best quality paper.

141
00:10:12,294 --> 00:10:13,700
六便士一包
Sixpence a packet.

142
00:10:13,737 --> 00:10:16,570
这人对信纸和信封都很讲究
Particular man in his stationery.

143
00:10:16,841 --> 00:10:18,000
华生
Watson.

144
00:10:18,972 --> 00:10:22,448
"今晚7时请到
Be at the third pillar from the left

145
00:10:22,486 --> 00:10:24,316
"Lyceum剧场外
outside the Lyceum Theatre

146
00:10:24,354 --> 00:10:25,787
"左数第三根柱子
tonight at seven o'clock.

147
00:10:26,109 --> 00:10:28,548
"如您怀疑 可偕友二人同来
If you are distrustful bring 2 friends.

148
00:10:28,586 --> 00:10:31,976
"您是受了委屈的女子 定将得到公道
You are a wronged woman and shall have justice.

149
00:10:32,488 --> 00:10:33,376
"别带警察来
Do not bring the police.

150
00:10:33,415 --> 00:10:35,155
"要不然 一切都是徒劳
If you do, all will be in vain.

151
00:10:35,192 --> 00:10:36,890
"您不知名的朋友"
Your unknown friend.

152
00:10:36,927 --> 00:10:39,424
嗯 有点小问题
Well, really,

153
00:10:39,462 --> 00:10:40,734
你打算怎么办 Morstan小姐?
this is a very pretty little problem.

154
00:10:40,772 --> 00:10:42,979
这正是我要问你的
What do you intend to do, Miss Morstan?

155
00:10:43,017 --> 00:10:44,809
我和你一起去
Well that is exactly what I want to ask you.

156
00:10:44,586 --> 00:10:46,945
Well then you and I shall go together.

157
00:10:46,443 --> 00:10:48,791
华生医生也很重要
Dr. Watson is the very man.

158
00:10:48,828 --> 00:10:51,532
上面说两位朋友
Your correspondent says 2 friends.

159
00:10:52,063 --> 00:10:53,517
但是他会去吗?
But would he come?

160
00:10:53,554 --> 00:10:54,652
我很荣幸
I shall be proud and happy

161
00:10:54,689 --> 00:10:56,912
为你效力
if I can be of any service.

162
00:10:58,450 --> 00:11:00,866
你们俩太好了
You are both very kind.

163
00:11:00,904 --> 00:11:02,050
我生活很孤独
I have led a retired life

164
00:11:02,088 --> 00:11:04,628
没有朋友可以相托
and have no friends whom I could appeal to.

165
00:11:05,023 --> 00:11:07,536
我6点来 行吗
If I am here at 6 it will do, I suppose?

166
00:11:07,574 --> 00:11:10,530
最晚6点 再见 Morstan小姐
Yes but you must not be later.

167
00:11:10,588 --> 00:11:12,281
再见 福尔摩斯先生
Goodbye Miss Morstan.

168
00:11:12,743 --> 00:11:13,914
再会
Goodbye Mr. Holmes.

169
00:11:13,951 --> 00:11:15,981
再会
Au revoir.

170
00:11:14,952 --> 00:11:16,409
Au revoir.

171
00:11:30,325 --> 00:11:31,715
买束花吧
Buy a flower dearie.

172
00:11:32,625 --> 00:11:34,100
买束花吧
Buy a flower.

173
00:11:34,827 --> 00:11:36,618
买束花吧
Aw come on dearie.

174
00:11:37,236 --> 00:11:38,821
抱歉
Excuse me.

175
00:11:40,269 --> 00:11:42,269
多有魅力的女人啊!
What a very attractive woman

176
00:11:44,475 --> 00:11:45,806
最重要的事就是
It is of the first importance

177
00:11:45,843 --> 00:11:47,549
不要让一个人的特质
not to allow your judgment to be biased

178
00:11:47,586 --> 00:11:49,475
影响了你的判断力
by personal qualities.

179
00:11:49,702 --> 00:11:51,434
一个委托人在我看来 仅仅是一个单元
A client to me is a mere unit,

180
00:11:51,471 --> 00:11:53,001
问题中的一个元素
a factor in of the problem.

181
00:11:53,002 --> 00:11:55,051
福尔摩斯 你真是个机器人
Holmes, you are a automaton

182
00:11:55,089 --> 00:11:55,694
一台计算器
and a calculating machine.

183
00:11:55,732 --> 00:12:00,139
有时你一点人情味儿都没有

184
00:11:57,630 --> 00:12:00,298
There's something positively inhuman in you at times.

185
00:12:00,178 --> 00:12:01,223
我告诉你
I assure you

186
00:12:01,260 --> 00:12:03,669
我生平所见最迷人的女人
the most winning woman I ever knew

187
00:12:03,705 --> 00:12:05,088
毒死了三个孩子
was hanged for poisoning 3 little children

188
00:12:05,125 --> 00:12:06,968
只为了骗取保险金
for their insurance money,

189
00:12:07,265 --> 00:12:09,538
我还认识一个模样无比讨厌的男人
and the most repellent man of my acquaintance

190
00:12:09,575 --> 00:12:12,439
却是个慈善家 捐赠大约25英镑
is a philanthropist who has spent nearly

191
00:12:12,551 --> 00:12:14,014
给伦敦的贫民
a quarter of a million upon the London poor.

192
00:12:14,018 --> 00:12:15,843
但是 在这件案子里...
However, in this case,

193
00:12:16,877 --> 00:12:18,414
我从不例外
I never make exceptions.

194
00:12:18,451 --> 00:12:20,115
定律没有例外
An exception disproves the rule.

195
00:12:20,152 --> 00:12:22,669
我要出去了 一小时后见
I'm going out. I'll see you in an hour.

196
00:12:37,768 --> 00:12:39,965
他在城里有朋友吗
<i>Had he any</i> <i>friends in town?</i>

197
00:12:40,002 --> 00:12:42,949
只有一个
<i>Only one that</i> <i>we know of,</i>

198
00:12:42,987 --> 00:12:45,952
叫Sholto少校 以前和他在一个团里
<i>Major Sholto of</i> <i>his own regiment.</i>

199
00:12:54,582 --> 00:12:56,334
案子没什么神秘的
There is no great mystery in this matter

200
00:12:56,371 --> 00:12:58,823
这些事实看来只有一种解释
the facts appear to admit of only one explanation.

201
00:12:58,861 --> 00:13:00,875
你已经弄清楚了吗?
Oh so you've solved it already?

202
00:13:00,913 --> 00:13:02,985
我发现在过期的泰晤士报上说
I have found,

203
00:13:03,022 --> 00:13:05,219
住在上诺伍德的Sholto少校
on consulting the back files of the Times,

204
00:13:05,257 --> 00:13:07,855
以前驻孟买陆军第三十四兵团
that Major Sholto, of Upper Norwood,

205
00:13:05,942 --> 00:13:07,673
late of the 34th Bombay Infantry,

206
00:13:07,892 --> 00:13:10,446
于6年前死亡
died just 6 years ago.

207
00:13:10,951 --> 00:13:13,791
Hudson太太 您在这儿 还真是碍手碍脚
Mrs. Hudson you're dreadfully under foot.

208
00:13:14,607 --> 00:13:15,754
也许我脑筋迟钝 福尔摩斯
I may be very obtuse, Holmes,

209
00:13:15,792 --> 00:13:17,500
可我看不出这有什么启示
but I fail to see what this suggests.

210
00:13:17,536 --> 00:13:18,540
真看不出?
Really?

211
00:13:18,578 --> 00:13:20,033
没想到
You surprise me.

212
00:13:20,071 --> 00:13:20,738
我们这么来看吧
Now look at it this way, then.

213
00:13:20,776 --> 00:13:23,221
Morstan上尉失踪了

214
00:13:22,464 --> 00:13:24,266
Captain Morstan disappears.

215
00:13:24,112 --> 00:13:26,258
在伦敦 只有一个人他可能去拜访
The only person in London

216
00:13:26,297 --> 00:13:27,651
那就是Sholto少校
whom he could have visited is Major Sholto.

217
00:13:27,688 --> 00:13:30,770
Sholto少校否认知道 他曾来过伦敦
Major Sholto denies having heard

218
00:13:30,856 --> 00:13:33,005
4年后Sholto死了
that he was even in London.

219
00:13:33,041 --> 00:13:35,527
他死后不到一个星期
4 years later Sholto dies.

220
00:13:33,664 --> 00:13:36,260
Within a week of his death

221
00:13:35,565 --> 00:13:37,362
Morstan上尉的女儿
Captain Morstan's daughter

222
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:39,187
收到了一份价值连城的礼物
receives a valuable present,

223
00:13:39,224 --> 00:13:41,047
以后每年收到一次
which is repeated from year to year

224
00:13:41,085 --> 00:13:43,053
现在她又收到一封信
and now culminates in a letter,

225
00:13:43,091 --> 00:13:45,715
说她是位受了委屈的女子
which describes her as a wronged woman.

226
00:13:45,752 --> 00:13:48,039
她受过什么委屈呢?
Now what wrong can it possibly refer to

227
00:13:48,076 --> 00:13:50,774
除了她丧父以外?
except this deprivation of her father?

228
00:13:50,812 --> 00:13:52,319
卷尺
Tape measure,

229
00:13:52,830 --> 00:13:53,925
枪
gun.

230
00:13:57,068 --> 00:13:58,310
为什么这些礼物
And why should these presents

231
00:13:58,348 --> 00:14:00,194
是在Sholto死后才送给她?
begin immediately after Sholto's death

232
00:14:00,231 --> 00:14:02,473
除非是Sholto的后人
unless it is that Sholto's heir

233
00:14:02,511 --> 00:14:03,723
知道其中的秘密
knows something of the mystery

234
00:14:03,760 --> 00:14:06,879
想要做些补偿
and desires to make compensation?

235
00:14:08,831 --> 00:14:10,483
准备好了吗 华生?
Are you ready Watson?

236
00:14:11,111 --> 00:14:12,846
就等你了
And waiting.

237
00:14:13,630 --> 00:14:15,290
你还有别的想法
Have you any alternative theory

238
00:14:15,327 --> 00:14:16,595
可以解释这些事实?
that will meet the facts?

239
00:14:16,633 --> 00:14:18,027
但 这真是个奇怪的补偿!
But what a strange compensation!

240
00:14:18,065 --> 00:14:19,760
太奇怪了!
And how strangely made!

241
00:14:19,994 --> 00:14:21,123
几点了?
What time is it?

242
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:23,864
6点15
It's a quarter past the hour.

243
00:14:35,727 --> 00:14:37,291
晚上好 Ellis
Evening Ellis.

244
00:14:37,329 --> 00:14:38,789
晚上好 先生
Evening sir.

245
00:14:40,432 --> 00:14:41,644
为什么那个人
Why should somebody

246
00:14:41,682 --> 00:14:42,778
现在才给她写信
write her a letter now,

247
00:14:42,815 --> 00:14:44,714
而不是6年前呢?
rather than 6 years ago?

248
00:14:44,961 --> 00:14:47,575
信上又说要还她公道
Again, the letter speaks of giving her justice.

249
00:14:47,613 --> 00:14:48,777
她可以得到什么公道呢?
What justice can she have?

250
00:14:48,814 --> 00:14:49,910
要说是她父亲还活着
It is too much to suppose

251
00:14:49,947 --> 00:14:51,385
那未免太乐观
that her father is still alive

252
00:14:51,422 --> 00:14:53,413
可是你又不知道
and there's no other injustice

253
00:14:53,451 --> 00:14:54,948
她还受过什么别的委屈
in her case that you know of.

254
00:14:54,985 --> 00:14:56,676
确实有些费解之处
There are difficulties

255
00:14:57,195 --> 00:14:59,636
但事情总是如此
but there are always difficulties.

256
00:15:04,592 --> 00:15:05,549
晚上好 福尔摩斯先生
Good evening Mr Holmes.

257
00:15:05,586 --> 00:15:07,246
-我想我没... -晚上好
I do hope I'm not...

258
00:15:07,403 --> 00:15:08,089
Good evening.

259
00:15:16,547 --> 00:15:17,463
顺便说一声
By the way,

260
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:20,613
在爸爸的书桌里找到张奇怪的纸
a curious paper was found in Papa's desk,

261
00:15:20,652 --> 00:15:22,308
没人能看懂
which nobody could understand.

262
00:15:22,345 --> 00:15:25,379
我想这未必和案子有关
I don't suppose it is of the slightest importance,

263
00:15:25,417 --> 00:15:27,148
但我想你可能愿意看一看
but I thought you might like to see it,

264
00:15:27,185 --> 00:15:28,831
所以我带来了
so I brought it with me.

265
00:15:30,024 --> 00:15:32,541
这纸像是印度产的
The paper appears to be of Indian manufacture.

266
00:15:32,579 --> 00:15:35,850
以前被钉在了板子上
At some point it's been pinned to a board.

267
00:15:37,809 --> 00:15:39,180
上面的图表像是
The diagram upon it appears to be the plan

268
00:15:39,217 --> 00:15:42,931
大建筑物草图的一部分

269
00:15:41,177 --> 00:15:43,358
of part of a large building

270
00:15:42,969 --> 00:15:46,304
里面有许多房间 走廊和过道
with numerous halls, corridors, and passages.

271
00:15:47,414 --> 00:15:50,468
上面用红笔画了个十字
There's a cross in red ink,

272
00:15:50,506 --> 00:15:55,559
在一边写着"从左边3.37"
and on the side is written '3.37 from left.'

273
00:15:55,596 --> 00:15:58,641
这有一个奇怪的象形文字
There is a curious hieroglyphic,

274
00:15:59,286 --> 00:16:01,780
四个签名
The sign of four

275
00:16:02,337 --> 00:16:04,240
Kartar Singh Indigo Singh
Kartar Singh, Indigo Singh,

276
00:16:04,277 --> 00:16:07,183
Jagodish Singh Jonathan Small
Jagodish Singh, Jonathan Small.

277
00:16:07,221 --> 00:16:10,752
这纸像是在钱夹里小心收藏过
It appears it has been kept carefully in a pocketbook,

278
00:16:10,789 --> 00:16:12,715
因为纸两边都很干净
for the one side is as clean as the other.

279
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:16,648
就是在他的钱夹里发现的
It was in his pocketbook that we found it.

280
00:16:16,851 --> 00:16:19,162
好好保管 Morstan小姐
Preserve it carefully, Miss Morstan.

281
00:16:20,207 --> 00:16:22,110
现在我觉得这个案子
I begin to suspect that this case may be

282
00:16:22,148 --> 00:16:24,488
似乎比最初想像的
much deeper and more subtle

283
00:16:24,525 --> 00:16:27,059
更深奥更复杂
than I ever first supposed.

284
00:17:13,108 --> 00:17:16,259
你们就是Morstan小姐 和她的同伴吗
Hey, are you the parties

285
00:17:16,297 --> 00:17:17,962
我就是Morstan小姐
who come with Miss Morstan?

286
00:17:17,999 --> 00:17:20,261
这两位是我的朋友
I'm Miss Morstan,

287
00:17:18,639 --> 00:17:20,546
and these 2 gentlemen are my companions.

288
00:17:20,298 --> 00:17:22,576
您得向我保证
I must ask you to give me your word

289
00:17:22,613 --> 00:17:24,059
您的两位同伴中
that neither of your companions

290
00:17:24,097 --> 00:17:25,494
没有警官
is a police officer.

291
00:17:25,532 --> 00:17:27,312
我保证
I give you my word.

292
00:18:06,632 --> 00:18:08,786
我的主人正在等候
Sahib awaits you.

293
00:18:10,181 --> 00:18:12,061
让他们进来 我的男仆
Show them in, Khitmutgar.

294
00:18:12,098 --> 00:18:14,417
直接把他们带到我这儿来
Show them straight in to me.

295
00:18:18,782 --> 00:18:22,528
愿意为您效劳 Morstan小姐
Your servant, Miss Morstan.

296
00:18:23,071 --> 00:18:26,530
愿意为两位效劳 先生们
Your servant, gentlemen.

297
00:18:27,281 --> 00:18:29,315
进来 进来 进来
Come in.

298
00:18:29,353 --> 00:18:32,432
进我这间小屋子来
Come in.

299
00:18:28,761 --> 00:18:29,661
Come in.

300
00:18:29,769 --> 00:18:33,278
Come in to my little sanctum.

301
00:18:32,907 --> 00:18:35,665
我想你们不会介意
I trust you have no objection

302
00:18:35,702 --> 00:18:38,659
烟草味儿吧?
to tobacco smoke?

303
00:18:38,696 --> 00:18:41,585
有香油味儿的
The balsamic odor

304
00:18:41,622 --> 00:18:44,554
东方烟草
of Eastern tobacco?

305
00:18:44,591 --> 00:18:47,488
我有点紧张
I am a little nervous

306
00:18:48,022 --> 00:18:52,983
我发现我的水烟袋是无上的...
and I find my hookah to be an invaluable...

307
00:19:07,411 --> 00:19:09,386
...镇静剂
sedative.

308
00:19:11,857 --> 00:19:14,406
打扰了 Sholto先生
You will excuse me Mr. Sholto

309
00:19:14,443 --> 00:19:17,958
您让我来这里
but I am here at your request

310
00:19:17,996 --> 00:19:19,417
是想告诉我
to learn something,

311
00:19:19,455 --> 00:19:21,644
什么事情呢?
which you desire to tell me?

312
00:19:21,681 --> 00:19:23,018
天有些晚了
It is getting very late and I should wish

313
00:19:23,056 --> 00:19:25,540
我希望谈话越简短越好
the interview to be as short as possible.

314
00:19:28,044 --> 00:19:30,721
嗯 要花些时间
Well it must take some time.

315
00:19:31,582 --> 00:19:36,592
因为我们要去诺伍德
For we have to go to Norwood

316
00:19:37,088 --> 00:19:39,525
见我哥哥Bartholomew
to see brother Bartholomew.

317
00:19:41,692 --> 00:19:44,542
我们都要去
We must all see

318
00:19:47,660 --> 00:19:52,490
也许我们可以说服
if we can get the better

319
00:19:51,335 --> 00:19:56,054
of brother Bartholomew.

320
00:19:53,063 --> 00:19:55,153
我哥哥Bartholomew

321
00:19:55,541 --> 00:19:58,063
他对我发了火
He is angry with me for

322
00:19:58,100 --> 00:20:05,276
因为我采取了我以为正确的行动

323
00:20:00,030 --> 00:20:06,243
taking the course that has seemed right to me.

324
00:20:05,313 --> 00:20:06,959
你们不知道
You cannot imagine

325
00:20:06,997 --> 00:20:10,619
当他生气的时候

326
00:20:08,656 --> 00:20:12,853
what a terrible fellow he is

327
00:20:12,266 --> 00:20:14,753
会是个多么难缠的人
when he is angry.

328
00:20:16,860 --> 00:20:18,425
要是我们去诺伍德
If we are to go to Norwood,

329
00:20:18,463 --> 00:20:21,098
最好还是现在就动身
it would perhaps be as well

330
00:20:21,135 --> 00:20:22,485
不
if we were start at once.

331
00:20:23,049 --> 00:20:25,959
那不合适
No.

332
00:20:23,682 --> 00:20:26,350
No that would hardly do.

333
00:20:25,996 --> 00:20:27,375
我不知道怎么和他说
I don't know what he would say

334
00:20:27,413 --> 00:20:29,793
要是我们这么唐突去见他
if we came upon him in that sudden way.

335
00:20:29,831 --> 00:20:33,195
我必须让你们做好准备
No I must prepare you

336
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:36,054
把咱们彼此的处境
by showing you where we all stand

337
00:20:37,056 --> 00:20:39,148
先谈一谈
to each other.

338
00:20:39,932 --> 00:20:46,880
首先我要把我知道的一些事实
I must lay the facts before you,

339
00:20:47,661 --> 00:20:50,793
告诉各位
as I know them myself.

340
00:20:55,688 --> 00:21:01,149
我父亲 就是已故的John Sholto少校
My father, the late Major John Sholto,

341
00:21:01,187 --> 00:21:07,831
大约11年前来到上诺伍德
came to live at Pondicherry Lodge

342
00:21:07,869 --> 00:21:11,791
定居于Pondicherry别墅
in Upper Norwood

343
00:21:09,143 --> 00:21:13,482
some 1 1 years ago.

344
00:21:12,941 --> 00:21:15,809
他在印度发了财
And he had prospered in India

345
00:21:15,846 --> 00:21:17,960
带回来了
and brought back with him

346
00:21:17,998 --> 00:21:20,585
一大笔钱
a considerable sum of money,

347
00:21:20,624 --> 00:21:24,097
还有一批珍贵的古董
a collection of valuable curiosities,

348
00:21:24,133 --> 00:21:28,355
和几个印度的仆人
and a staff of native servants.

349
00:21:28,394 --> 00:21:30,150
因为这些
With these advantages

350
00:21:30,187 --> 00:21:33,643
他生活得很富裕
he lived in great luxury.

351
00:21:33,680 --> 00:21:36,810
那时我哥哥和我正在上大学
My brother and I were at university at the time.

352
00:21:36,848 --> 00:21:39,212
然而 我们确实清楚
We did know, however,

353
00:21:39,249 --> 00:21:41,196
有些秘密
that some mystery,

354
00:21:41,233 --> 00:21:43,703
某种存在的危险
some positive danger,

355
00:21:43,741 --> 00:21:47,081
藏在我父亲的心里
overhung our father.

356
00:21:49,188 --> 00:21:51,860
他非常害怕
He was very fearful

357
00:21:51,898 --> 00:21:54,661
独自一人外出
of going out alone,

358
00:21:54,697 --> 00:21:58,344
他雇了2个职业拳击手
and he employed 2 prizefighters

359
00:21:58,382 --> 00:21:59,507
保护他
to guard him.

360
00:21:59,545 --> 00:22:02,940
Williams 今晚送你们来的那个人
Williams, who drove you here tonight,

361
00:22:02,977 --> 00:22:04,448
就是其中之一
was one of them.

362
00:22:04,486 --> 00:22:05,841
出于某种原因
For some reason,

363
00:22:05,878 --> 00:22:07,714
他从不告诉我们
he never told anyone,

364
00:22:08,362 --> 00:22:13,431
我父亲对装有木腿的人格外提防
my father had a marked aversion

365
00:22:10,882 --> 00:22:14,557
to men with wooden legs.

366
00:22:13,978 --> 00:22:17,745
有一次他竟然开枪打伤了
On one occasion

367
00:22:16,204 --> 00:22:18,420
he actually fired his revolver

368
00:22:17,783 --> 00:22:20,296
一个只有一条腿的人
at a one-legged man.

369
00:22:20,816 --> 00:22:24,683
那人只不过是个平常的商贩
A harmless tradesman as it turned out.

370
00:22:31,303 --> 00:22:37,009
我记得当时我们 赔了很大一笔钱才了事
I remember we have to pay

371
00:22:34,395 --> 00:22:37,869
a considerable sum to hush it up.

372
00:22:38,917 --> 00:22:41,933
然后 突然
Then suddenly

373
00:22:44,103 --> 00:22:48,080
我父亲收到了一封信
my father received a letter

374
00:22:49,312 --> 00:22:54,077
那封信对他是很大的打击
It was a great shock to him.

375
00:23:05,481 --> 00:23:06,685
出去
Out.

376
00:23:07,457 --> 00:23:09,094
从房间出去!
Out of the room!

377
00:23:09,541 --> 00:23:11,912
从房间出去!
Out of the room!

378
00:23:25,654 --> 00:23:29,039
信上说了什么
What was in the letter

379
00:23:30,852 --> 00:23:33,560
我们永远不知道
we could never discover?

380
00:23:35,331 --> 00:23:38,018
我父亲多年身患
For years my father had suffered

381
00:23:38,056 --> 00:23:41,136
脾脏肿大的毛病

382
00:23:39,648 --> 00:23:42,422
with an enlarged spleen

383
00:23:41,905 --> 00:23:43,372
从那时起
and from that moment on

384
00:23:43,409 --> 00:23:45,841
他的病情变得更糟
he became rapidly worse.

385
00:23:46,529 --> 00:23:51,408
一天晚上医生通知我们说 没希望了
But one night the doctor informed us there was no hope

386
00:23:51,446 --> 00:23:56,327
要我们听他的最后的遗嘱
and that he wished to make a last communication to us.

387
00:23:59,298 --> 00:24:01,397
我亲爱的家人
My dear family,

388
00:24:03,801 --> 00:24:08,239
我在印度的时候

389
00:24:06,640 --> 00:24:09,556
when we were in India

390
00:24:08,868 --> 00:24:12,865
我的朋友 Morstan和我
my friend, Morstan and I,

391
00:24:13,396 --> 00:24:16,334
得到了一大笔的
came into possession

392
00:24:16,371 --> 00:24:18,877
宝物
of a considerable treasure.

393
00:24:20,282 --> 00:24:24,988
我把它们带回了这里
I brought it home with me to this house,

394
00:24:26,119 --> 00:24:28,644
至今还在这
where it's still alive.

395
00:24:32,437 --> 00:24:35,627
那天 Morstan先生
On the day, Mr. Morstan,

396
00:24:36,324 --> 00:24:39,060
从印度回来
had arrived home from the East.

397
00:24:39,825 --> 00:24:44,784
他直接找到这里
He came straight to this house

398
00:24:45,409 --> 00:24:48,654
指责我独吞了财宝
to claim his share.

399
00:24:48,691 --> 00:24:51,598
我们发过誓 Sholto
We gave our word Sholto.

400
00:24:51,635 --> 00:24:52,572
一个诺言
A promise.

401
00:24:52,610 --> 00:24:54,823
我们发过毒誓
We gave our word and our oath.

402
00:24:54,861 --> 00:24:57,259
另一时间
another time,

403
00:24:57,296 --> 00:24:59,240
另一种生活 另一个世界
another life, another world,

404
00:24:59,278 --> 00:25:01,076
一个庄严的诺言
a solemn promise.

405
00:25:01,113 --> 00:25:03,744
你背叛了我 Morstan
You tried to betray me Morstan.

406
00:25:03,781 --> 00:25:06,548
要是你敢背叛我...
If you dare to cross me...

407
00:25:10,699 --> 00:25:12,253
上帝
My God.

408
00:25:13,479 --> 00:25:15,121
他死了 Altada
The man is dead Altada.

409
00:25:15,158 --> 00:25:17,171
不用害怕 先生
You have nothing to fear Sir.

410
00:25:17,209 --> 00:25:19,289
下面的我来安排
I will arrange everything.

411
00:25:19,325 --> 00:25:23,582
一会他就弄完了 Morstan小姐
And soon it was done Miss Morstan,

412
00:25:23,620 --> 00:25:26,100
当然是极其秘密的
in secrecy of course

413
00:25:26,138 --> 00:25:29,736
但是不失尊重
but with respect.

414
00:25:29,773 --> 00:25:31,521
这确实很可耻 Sholto先生
This is disgraceful Mister Sholto.

415
00:25:31,558 --> 00:25:34,829
你父亲的行为是不可原谅的
Your father's behavior was quite unforgivable.

416
00:25:34,867 --> 00:25:37,123
拜托 医生
Please Doctor.

417
00:25:39,874 --> 00:25:41,624
我打心底知道
I knew in my heart

418
00:25:41,661 --> 00:25:44,147
他已死了
that he was dead.

419
00:25:46,014 --> 00:25:48,498
但我父亲并不孤单
My father was not alone then.

420
00:25:51,816 --> 00:25:54,280
我很高兴他没受罪
And I'm glad he didn't suffer.

421
00:25:54,318 --> 00:25:56,930
你很勇敢 Morstan小姐
You're very brave Miss Morstan.

422
00:25:58,199 --> 00:26:01,392
现在我所关心的是那场争吵
What concerns me now

423
00:26:01,430 --> 00:26:02,851
我不能想象
is the wishing for this quarrel.

424
00:26:02,888 --> 00:26:05,593
我父亲是怎么卷进这个财宝的
I cannot imagine how my father

425
00:26:04,414 --> 00:26:07,010
came to be involved with that treasure.

426
00:26:06,306 --> 00:26:11,162
恐怕事情还不清楚 Morstan小姐
I'm afraid that is not clear Miss Morstan

427
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:12,360
我只能告诉你
I can only tell you

428
00:26:14,019 --> 00:26:21,467
我父亲对我们说的
my father's instructions concerning it.

429
00:26:26,863 --> 00:26:31,806
贪...婪

430
00:26:30,570 --> 00:26:32,549
The greed.

431
00:26:32,912 --> 00:26:37,415
可憎的贪婪一生折磨着我
accursed greed that has been

432
00:26:35,788 --> 00:26:38,491
my besetting thing throughout my life

433
00:26:37,454 --> 00:26:41,236
我抢走了她的财产
has robbed her of the treasure.

434
00:26:42,073 --> 00:26:45,387
至少有一半是她的
Half of which, at least,

435
00:26:45,425 --> 00:26:47,375
应该还给她
should be hers.

436
00:26:48,447 --> 00:26:57,497
你们看这串项链
You see that chaplet there.

437
00:26:57,534 --> 00:27:04,968
我想把它送给她

438
00:26:59,231 --> 00:27:05,587
I had the design of sending it to her

439
00:27:05,006 --> 00:27:11,746
但是又舍不得
but could not bear to part with it.

440
00:27:12,490 --> 00:27:13,785
你们
You

441
00:27:14,490 --> 00:27:16,623
我的儿子们
my sons

442
00:27:16,977 --> 00:27:19,873
一定要让Morstan小姐
must see that Miss Morstan

443
00:27:19,911 --> 00:27:33,516
得到属于她的一份
gets her share of the treasure.

444
00:27:37,397 --> 00:27:38,854
把他赶走
Get him away.

445
00:27:40,181 --> 00:27:44,682
看在上帝的份上 把他赶走
For Christ's sake get him away.

446
00:27:44,996 --> 00:27:48,083
我们冲到窗前 跑到花园中
We ran to the window and out into the garden

447
00:27:48,121 --> 00:27:51,719
但是那个人已经没了
but the intruder was gone.

448
00:27:51,756 --> 00:27:54,687
我父亲死了
My father was dead.

449
00:27:54,725 --> 00:27:58,808
不久我们就得到了更确切的证明
We soon had more striking proof that there were

450
00:27:58,844 --> 00:28:02,474
有秘密组织在盯着我们
secret agencies that work all around us.

451
00:28:02,513 --> 00:28:07,949
第二天有人闯进我父亲的卧室
The next day my father's bedroom was broken into

452
00:28:07,986 --> 00:28:13,914
这个被放在了他的胸前
and this was fixed to his chest.

453
00:28:16,862 --> 00:28:18,862
很关键
Remarkable.

454
00:28:18,899 --> 00:28:22,618
这是印度锡克教数字4的标记
It is the Sikkh symbol for the numeral 4.

455
00:28:26,996 --> 00:28:28,951
这张纸是什么意思
What the paper means

456
00:28:28,989 --> 00:28:31,568
还有我们神秘的来访者是谁
and who our secret visitor or visitors were

457
00:28:31,605 --> 00:28:34,338
我们都不知道
we never found out.

458
00:28:39,234 --> 00:28:42,423
我哥哥和我都很兴奋
And my brother and I were much excited

459
00:28:42,460 --> 00:28:43,684
你们能想象出来
as you could imagine

460
00:28:43,723 --> 00:28:45,478
都是由于我父亲说的财宝
of the treasure that my father had spoken

461
00:28:45,515 --> 00:28:47,771
但是 我们竭尽所能都没有找到
but try as we might we couldn't find it.

462
00:28:47,808 --> 00:28:50,164
我们有些发狂 只要想到收藏宝藏的地方
It was maddened to think that the hiding place

463
00:28:50,201 --> 00:28:53,323
就在他临终的嘴边
was on his very lips when he died.

464
00:28:53,361 --> 00:28:57,309
从这个项链上 我们就可以
We could judge the splendor of the riches

465
00:28:57,347 --> 00:28:59,819
看出这批财宝的贵重
by the chaplet, which he had taken out.

466
00:28:59,856 --> 00:29:02,519
这几颗珍珠都很值钱
The pearls were evidently of great value,

467
00:29:02,558 --> 00:29:06,598
我哥哥不愿意把它们给她
and my brother was averse to part with them,

468
00:29:06,634 --> 00:29:09,647
在对待朋友上
for, between friends,

469
00:29:09,686 --> 00:29:13,436
他也有点我父亲的缺点
he was a little inclined to my father's fault.

470
00:29:13,474 --> 00:29:16,579
我所能做的只是规劝他
And it was all I could do was to persuade him

471
00:29:16,617 --> 00:29:18,696
允许我每隔一段时间给Morstan小姐
to allow me to send Miss Morstan

472
00:29:18,733 --> 00:29:21,848
一颗拆下来的珍珠
a detached pearl at regular intervals

473
00:29:21,886 --> 00:29:24,441
这样她就不会生活拮据了
so that she would not feel destitute.

474
00:29:24,478 --> 00:29:27,013
真是好心眼
It was a kindly thought.

475
00:29:28,032 --> 00:29:30,870
你真是太好心了
No it was very good of you.

476
00:29:32,730 --> 00:29:35,217
我们只是你的托管人
We were your trustees

477
00:29:35,255 --> 00:29:37,603
这是我的看法
that was the way I looked at it,

478
00:29:37,640 --> 00:29:41,189
虽然我哥哥和我看法不同
although my brother

479
00:29:41,226 --> 00:29:44,375
我们自己有很多钱
did not altogether see it in that light.

480
00:29:42,013 --> 00:29:44,966
We had plenty of money ourselves.

481
00:29:44,412 --> 00:29:48,818
用卑劣的手段
It would have been in such bad taste

482
00:29:48,856 --> 00:29:51,646
对待一位年轻的女士
to have treated a young lady

483
00:29:51,683 --> 00:29:54,842
实在是情理难容
in so scurvy a fashion.

484
00:29:56,386 --> 00:29:57,637
就在昨天
Yesterday an event

485
00:29:57,674 --> 00:30:02,945
发生了一件极其重要的事

486
00:29:59,579 --> 00:30:03,325
of extreme importance occurred.

487
00:30:06,810 --> 00:30:11,537
我们找到财宝了
We, found of the treasure.

488
00:30:11,574 --> 00:30:16,222
因此 我立即联系了Morstan小姐
Hence my instant communication to you Miss Morstan.

489
00:30:16,260 --> 00:30:20,172
我们现在要做的就是去诺伍德
Now all we have to do is to drive to Norwood

490
00:30:20,210 --> 00:30:23,687
向他索要我们应得的那份
and claim our share.

491
00:30:26,214 --> 00:30:28,873
在他眼中 我们也许是
We shall be expected,

492
00:30:28,911 --> 00:30:33,326
不受欢迎的客人
if not entirely welcome, visitors.

493
00:30:33,363 --> 00:30:36,653
你从头到尾做得都很好 Sholto先生
You have done well from first to last Mr. Sholto.

494
00:30:40,984 --> 00:30:45,139
我身体很弱
My health is somewhat fragile.

495
00:30:45,176 --> 00:30:50,167
只能算个病人
I am compelled to be a valetudinarian.

496
00:30:50,204 --> 00:30:53,110
请

497
00:30:52,240 --> 00:30:54,527
Please?

498
00:31:05,621 --> 00:31:08,643
花园的每个角落我们都挖过
We dug up every inch of the garden

499
00:31:08,680 --> 00:31:11,861
没有任何发现
without discovering anything.

500
00:31:13,758 --> 00:31:16,454
我哥哥Bartholomew很聪明
Brother Bartholomew is such a clever fellow.

501
00:31:17,484 --> 00:31:19,175
你们知道他是怎样
Do you know how he found out

502
00:31:19,213 --> 00:31:20,953
发现宝藏的吗
where the treasure was?

503
00:31:20,990 --> 00:31:22,128
说
Tell me.

504
00:31:22,807 --> 00:31:24,711
他测量了每个角落
He made measurements everywhere,

505
00:31:24,749 --> 00:31:25,938
从上面
all along the top,

506
00:31:25,975 --> 00:31:28,054
侧面 里面
along the side, inside and he found out

507
00:31:28,091 --> 00:31:32,358
最后在离房顶4英尺的地方

508
00:31:29,944 --> 00:31:33,418
he was 4 foot out at the top.

509
00:31:32,396 --> 00:31:35,694
我们发现了父亲建的一个小顶楼
We found our father made a false room

510
00:31:35,733 --> 00:31:40,801
他在板条灰泥天花板上打了个洞

511
00:31:37,770 --> 00:31:41,896
So he smashed through the lath and the plaster

512
00:31:41,598 --> 00:31:44,081
宝箱就在...
and there was the treasure chest

513
00:31:44,119 --> 00:31:46,682
椽木上
lying across the rafters.

514
00:31:46,720 --> 00:31:48,717
他估算了一下
He has computed the value of the treasure

515
00:31:48,754 --> 00:31:50,623
差不多超过...

516
00:31:50,661 --> 00:31:54,574
50万英镑
to be more than one half million sterling.

517
00:31:55,580 --> 00:31:58,390
[scream]

518
00:31:58,178 --> 00:31:59,587
是Bernstone夫人
It's Mrs. Bernstone.

519
00:32:00,077 --> 00:32:02,869
Bernstone夫人是这房子里唯一的女人
Mrs. Bernstone is the only lady in the house

520
00:32:02,907 --> 00:32:04,871
在这等着
wait here.

521
00:32:16,911 --> 00:32:20,862
Thaddeus先生 真高兴您来了
Oh, Mr. Thaddeus I'm so glad you've come!

522
00:32:21,589 --> 00:32:24,084
真高兴您来了 先生
I'm so glad you've come, sir!

523
00:32:27,396 --> 00:32:29,821
真是个奇怪的地方!
What a strange place!

524
00:32:32,127 --> 00:32:36,120
好像全英国的鼹鼠都跑到这来了
It looks as if all the moles in England

525
00:32:34,571 --> 00:32:36,858
have been let loose in it.

526
00:32:38,863 --> 00:32:41,364
Bartholomew好像出事了
There's something amiss with Bartholomew

527
00:32:41,402 --> 00:32:42,739
进屋去!
Into the house!

528
00:32:57,532 --> 00:33:00,725
上帝保佑 看您这张甜美安静的脸多好
bless your sweet, calm face.

529
00:33:00,763 --> 00:33:03,862
我这一天可真是受够了
Oh, but I have been sorely tried this day.

530
00:33:04,251 --> 00:33:05,905
怎么了 Bernstone夫人?
How Mrs. Bernstone?

531
00:33:06,472 --> 00:33:09,115
Bartholomew先生把自己关在屋里
Mr. Bartholomew shut himself in his room

532
00:33:09,153 --> 00:33:11,181
没和我说一句话
and I can't get a word out of him.

533
00:33:11,218 --> 00:33:13,248
没有睡觉
His bed hasn't been slept in

534
00:33:13,286 --> 00:33:16,761
也没下楼吃过东西
and he hasn't been down for any food.

535
00:33:16,798 --> 00:33:19,569
他工作的时候我不敢打扰他
I dare not disturb him at his work.

536
00:33:19,606 --> 00:33:21,975
你知道他工作时候的样子
You know what he's like when it's his work.

537
00:33:22,012 --> 00:33:24,232
照顾好她 Morstan小姐
Look after her Miss Morstan.

538
00:33:30,606 --> 00:33:32,124
来 冷静一下
There, there do try to calm down.

539
00:33:32,162 --> 00:33:34,293
瞧 一切都会好的
Look I'm sure everything will be all right.

540
00:33:34,330 --> 00:33:36,720
希望你是对的 小姐
I do hope your right Miss.

541
00:33:36,756 --> 00:33:38,603
坐这里
Sit down over there.

542
00:33:47,684 --> 00:33:49,419
过来
Come.

543
00:34:00,612 --> 00:34:01,720
哪个门?
Which is the door?

544
00:34:37,880 --> 00:34:40,496
里面情况很糟糕 华生
There's something devilish in this, Watson.

545
00:35:19,143 --> 00:35:21,693
又是四签名
The sign of the four again.

546
00:35:21,731 --> 00:35:23,728
这一切是怎么回事?
What in God's name does it all mean?

547
00:35:23,765 --> 00:35:25,754
谋杀
It means murder.

548
00:35:28,047 --> 00:35:33,386
昨晚我们把财宝搬下来 放在那里

549
00:35:30,606 --> 00:35:32,621
We brought the treasure down there last night.

550
00:35:35,286 --> 00:35:36,634
现在不见了
Now its gone.

551
00:35:36,672 --> 00:35:37,812
那是几点的事
What time is that?

552
00:35:37,849 --> 00:35:41,679
不...不知道

553
00:35:39,754 --> 00:35:42,385
I don't know.

554
00:35:41,826 --> 00:35:45,639
我想是6点或是7点
I think six, or seven.

555
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:50,883
我走后听见他锁门了

556
00:35:47,927 --> 00:35:52,682
I heard him lock the door after I left.

557
00:35:52,427 --> 00:35:56,912
我一定是最后见到他活着的人
I must have been the last person to see him alive.

558
00:35:57,785 --> 00:35:59,371
现在他死了
And now he's dead

559
00:36:04,155 --> 00:36:06,508
你想是我干的?
you think I did it?

560
00:36:06,545 --> 00:36:08,527
我没有 为什么我要...
I didn't, why should I,

561
00:36:08,564 --> 00:36:09,518
我不会让你...
I wouldn't have wanted you...

562
00:36:09,555 --> 00:36:10,869
我不会请你来...
I wouldn't have asked you to...

563
00:36:10,908 --> 00:36:12,121
我要疯了

564
00:36:12,159 --> 00:36:14,338
冷静 冷静 冷静  Sholto先生
I'll go mad.

565
00:36:14,375 --> 00:36:15,679
我建议你报警
Gentle, gently, gentle Mr. Sholto.

566
00:36:15,716 --> 00:36:17,930
把你知道的一切告诉他们
I suggest that you go down to the police station

567
00:36:17,968 --> 00:36:19,978
我们等你回来
and tell them everything that you know.

568
00:36:18,502 --> 00:36:20,967
We shall wait here until you return.

569
00:36:20,322 --> 00:36:23,078
福尔摩斯 看这个
Holmes look at this.

570
00:36:23,115 --> 00:36:24,211
小心
Careful!

571
00:36:24,248 --> 00:36:26,532
上面有毒
Forgive me, its poisoned.

572
00:36:28,027 --> 00:36:30,471
华生 我们还有些时间
Well Watson we have a little time

573
00:36:30,509 --> 00:36:32,173
弄清楚整个过程
let's make the most of it.

574
00:36:32,210 --> 00:36:34,749
这件事真是扑朔迷离
Awe this is an Insoluble mystery to me.

575
00:36:34,787 --> 00:36:36,500
不止没搞明白 反而越来越糊涂了
It grows darker instead of clearer.

576
00:36:36,538 --> 00:36:38,234
不 不 不 马上就会水落石出
No, no, no, no it clears every instant.

577
00:36:38,271 --> 00:36:39,742
我只要再弄清几个环节
I only require a few missing links

578
00:36:39,779 --> 00:36:42,243
就可以把整个案子串联起来
to have an entirely connected case.

579
00:36:42,583 --> 00:36:44,152
现在案子看上去很简单了
Simple as the case seems now

580
00:36:44,189 --> 00:36:47,098
还有几件事不明白
there may be something deeper underlying it.

581
00:36:47,135 --> 00:36:49,348
这些人怎么进来的
How did these people come

582
00:36:49,385 --> 00:36:50,347
怎么出去的
and how did they go?

583
00:36:50,385 --> 00:36:51,630
这些人?
People?

584
00:36:51,668 --> 00:36:53,758
要从这种地方搬走财宝箱
Well it takes more than one, perhaps more than 2

585
00:36:53,796 --> 00:36:56,867
需要不止一个人 或许两人以上
to remove a heavy treasure chest

586
00:36:56,905 --> 00:36:59,631
门从昨晚就没开过
from a place like this.

587
00:36:58,119 --> 00:37:00,655
The door hasn't been opened since last night.

588
00:37:00,074 --> 00:37:02,125
那这些窗户呢?
So how about these windows?

589
00:37:08,398 --> 00:37:10,658
插销在里面
Snibbed on the inside.

590
00:37:11,380 --> 00:37:12,947
没有合叶
No hinges.

591
00:37:12,984 --> 00:37:14,796
屋顶离的很远
Roof quite out of reach.

592
00:37:14,834 --> 00:37:16,990
附近没有排水管
No drainpipe near.

593
00:37:17,972 --> 00:37:20,886
有人可能从这进来 看 华生
Yet someone has entered this way look.

594
00:37:21,186 --> 00:37:23,156
窗台上有足迹
Watson.

595
00:37:22,084 --> 00:37:25,273
See that a scuff on the sill.

596
00:37:30,711 --> 00:37:32,438
看这个 华生
Look at this Watson

597
00:37:33,992 --> 00:37:35,888
这儿和这儿
and this and this.

598
00:37:35,926 --> 00:37:37,756
这真是个非常好的证据
This is a very pretty demonstration.

599
00:37:37,794 --> 00:37:40,041
但那不是脚印
But that's not a footmark.

