00:59:52,796 --> 00:59:54,729
他们是我的客人
they are my guests.

993
00:59:58,939 --> 01:00:01,005
听着 帽子摘了
Look, hats off.

994
01:00:01,043 --> 01:00:02,415
我收到您的消息了
I've got your message.

995
01:00:02,453 --> 01:00:04,124
就带他们来了
I brought 'em on sharp.

996
01:00:04,161 --> 01:00:07,740
车费三先令六便士
3 bob and a tenner for the tickets.

997
01:00:11,975 --> 01:00:13,899
Wiggins 以后有事
Now Wiggins, in future

998
01:00:13,937 --> 01:00:16,547
他们就向你汇报 你再告诉我
they can report to you and you to me.

999
01:00:16,585 --> 01:00:19,068
我这屋子容不下这么多人
I cannot have the house invaded in this way.

1000
01:00:19,105 --> 01:00:20,683
别动
Oye stop that.

1001
01:00:22,814 --> 01:00:24,035
抱歉
Sorry.

1002
01:00:25,927 --> 01:00:29,826
我要你们找一艘叫"曙光"号的汽艇
Now I want you to find the steamboat Aurora.

1003
01:00:29,863 --> 01:00:31,082
"曙光"号
Aurora.

1004
01:00:31,120 --> 01:00:34,194
是Mordecai Smith家的
Owner Mordecai Smith,

1005
01:00:34,748 --> 01:00:36,844
黑底有金边
black with gold trim.

1006
01:00:36,882 --> 01:00:38,162
从Richmond到Gravesend
Richmond to Gravesend

1007
01:00:38,199 --> 01:00:39,620
在河的两岸查找
both sides of the river.

1008
01:00:39,658 --> 01:00:40,848
好的 先生
Fine sir.

1009
01:00:40,885 --> 01:00:42,232
报酬是多少?
How much?

1010
01:00:42,270 --> 01:00:44,141
老规矩
Old scale of pay

1011
01:00:44,178 --> 01:00:46,871
找到船的孩子多给一个几尼
a guinea to the boy who finds the boat.

1012
01:00:47,507 --> 01:00:50,215
这是预付给你们一天的工钱
Here is a day in advance.

1013
01:01:05,920 --> 01:01:07,661
只要这船还停在水上
If the launch is above water

1014
01:01:07,698 --> 01:01:09,616
这些非正规军就能找到她
the irregulars will find her.

1015
01:01:10,133 --> 01:01:13,143
他们无处不到 一切都逃过他们的眼睛
They can go everywhere, see everything.

1016
01:01:16,904 --> 01:01:20,331
咱们这个问题看来不难解决
If our man had an easy task

1017
01:01:21,006 --> 01:01:22,951
一只腿的人并不多见
just as ours ought to be.

1018
01:01:22,989 --> 01:01:25,273
另一个人也很特殊
One-legged men are not so common

1019
01:01:23,688 --> 01:01:25,738
and this other man must be unique.

1020
01:01:27,316 --> 01:01:30,157
安达曼群岛的土著居民
The aborigines of the Andaman Islands

1021
01:01:30,194 --> 01:01:31,481
或许可以称得上是
may perhaps claim the distinction

1022
01:01:31,519 --> 01:01:35,400
世界最矮小的种族了
of being the smallest race upon this earth.

1023
01:01:36,121 --> 01:01:39,238
他们生性凶猛 怪癖 难以交往
They are a fierce, morose,

1024
01:01:39,620 --> 01:01:42,031
但如果得到他们的信任
and intractable people,

1025
01:01:40,348 --> 01:01:41,841
though capable of forming

1026
01:01:42,068 --> 01:01:45,107
他们会成为至死不渝的朋友
the most devoted friendships

1027
01:01:43,583 --> 01:01:45,942
when their confidence has once been gained.

1028
01:01:45,820 --> 01:01:49,901
对于船只的遇难水手来说 他们永远是个祸害
They have always been a terror to shipwrecked crews,

1029
01:01:50,499 --> 01:01:54,058
往往被他们用绑着石头的木棒击碎脑袋
braining the survivors with their stone-headed clubs

1030
01:01:54,095 --> 01:01:56,717
或是用...
or shooting them with

1031
01:01:59,527 --> 01:02:02,043
用毒箭刺死
with poisoned arrows.

1032
01:02:02,774 --> 01:02:05,806
通常屠杀之后
These massacres are usually concluded

1033
01:02:07,496 --> 01:02:10,063
将人肉作为盛宴
by a cannibal feast.

1034
01:02:14,976 --> 01:02:19,147
这真是一群"和善"的人啊
Nice, amiable people.

1035
01:02:35,625 --> 01:02:38,537
什么时候吃晚饭 福尔摩斯先生?
And what time would you like for dinner Mr. Holmes?

1036
01:02:38,575 --> 01:02:40,513
后天8点半
Half past eight the day after tomorrow.

1037
01:02:52,607 --> 01:02:53,791
你会撑不住的
You'll wear yourself out old man.

1038
01:02:53,828 --> 01:02:55,678
我听见你整晚上都踱来踱去的
I heard you marching about all night.

1039
01:02:56,688 --> 01:02:58,629
你真的需要些休息了
You really must get some rest.

1040
01:02:58,667 --> 01:02:59,866
我睡不着
I can't sleep.

1041
01:02:59,903 --> 01:03:02,508
这个恶魔似的问题一直困扰着我
This infernal problem is consuming me.

1042
01:03:02,546 --> 01:03:03,924
没有消息?
No news?

1043
01:03:04,262 --> 01:03:06,721
没有 什么都没有
None.

1044
01:03:06,759 --> 01:03:08,791
河的两岸都搜过了
None whatsoever.

1045
01:03:08,827 --> 01:03:10,422
Smith夫人也没有他丈夫的消息
The whole river has been searched from both sides.

1046
01:03:10,461 --> 01:03:14,750
其他的问题都解决了
Mrs. Smith has not heard from her husband,

1047
01:03:10,783 --> 01:03:12,928
it's too much.

1048
01:03:13,043 --> 01:03:15,058
To be balked by some petty obstacle

1049
01:03:14,787 --> 01:03:17,035
就是这个问题一直阻碍着我们
when all else has been overcome.

1050
01:03:47,300 --> 01:03:48,542
看见什么了吗?
See anything?

1051
01:03:49,883 --> 01:03:51,510
什么都没有
No nothing.

1052
01:04:22,842 --> 01:04:26,180
快下船 否则我就要来赶你了!
Shove off.

1053
01:04:24,905 --> 01:04:27,999
Or you'll feel the back of my hand.

1054
01:04:30,626 --> 01:04:34,340
"曙光"号

1055
01:04:42,470 --> 01:04:45,101
我不想再说一遍了 孩子
I'm not going to tell you again boy.

1056
01:05:19,828 --> 01:05:22,286
多漂亮的一搜小船
A nice little craft.

1057
01:05:23,271 --> 01:05:24,613
是条不错的船
Aye, she's a good boat this.

1058
01:05:24,651 --> 01:05:26,955
我们在这里把它造好的
We built her right in this yard.

1059
01:05:26,992 --> 01:05:28,680
在河里行得最快的船
Fastest boat on the river.

1060
01:05:28,717 --> 01:05:30,811
为什么停进来?
What she in for?

1061
01:05:30,850 --> 01:05:32,393
维修一下方向舵
Repairs to her rudder.

1062
01:05:32,430 --> 01:05:33,819
这是惯例
That's the order.

1063
01:05:33,857 --> 01:05:35,826
在它身上找不到任何差错
I can't find anything amiss with it.

1064
01:05:35,863 --> 01:05:40,162
今晚六点我们的船要出坞了
I want her in the water

1065
01:05:38,261 --> 01:05:41,035
by six o'clock tonight.

1066
01:05:40,493 --> 01:05:43,965
加满煤 全速前进
Fully coaled and steam up.

1067
01:05:44,002 --> 01:05:45,081
Smith先生 准备好了
Right Mr. Smith she'll be ready.

1068
01:05:45,118 --> 01:05:49,126
6点要全速前进

1069
01:05:47,132 --> 01:05:49,633
Six o'clock sharp, mind,

1070
01:05:49,164 --> 01:05:53,096
这两位先生已经等不急了
for 2 gentlemen that'll not be kept waiting.

1071
01:05:53,593 --> 01:05:54,705
好的
Right.

1072
01:05:58,715 --> 01:06:01,058
就是这个诺伍德案 医生
It's this Norwood case Doctor.

1073
01:06:01,095 --> 01:06:03,567
总是有些麻烦困扰着我
I have a great deal to worry and try me.

1074
01:06:03,606 --> 01:06:06,143
这桩案子就是之一
And this case is a very dark one too.

1075
01:06:06,962 --> 01:06:07,628
谢谢
Thank you.

1076
01:06:07,666 --> 01:06:10,679
我很感激福尔摩斯先生的帮助
I shall be most grateful for Mr. Holmes' help.

1077
01:06:10,716 --> 01:06:11,987
你的朋友是个好人
Your friend is a wonderful man

1078
01:06:12,025 --> 01:06:13,438
谁也比不上他
and not to be beat.

1079
01:06:15,537 --> 01:06:17,838
也许你要等很长时间
Well you maybe in for a long wait.

1080
01:06:17,876 --> 01:06:20,267
我不这么想
Nope I don't think so.

1081
01:06:21,613 --> 01:06:23,527
"马上去贝克街
Go to Baker Street at once.

1082
01:06:23,564 --> 01:06:25,985
"要是我没回来 等着我
If I've not returned, wait for me.

1083
01:06:26,024 --> 01:06:28,763
"我已找到Sholto案匪徒的踪迹
I am close on the track of the Sholto gang.

1084
01:06:28,799 --> 01:06:30,286
"要是想看到本案的结局
Come with us tonight

1085
01:06:30,324 --> 01:06:31,437
"今晚和我们同去"
if you want to be in at the kill.

1086
01:06:31,473 --> 01:06:36,516
不错 他又找到线索了
Good.

1087
01:06:33,566 --> 01:06:36,826
So he's on the scent again?

1088
01:06:36,555 --> 01:06:39,283
之前他也查错了方向?
He's been at fault too has he?

1089
01:06:39,320 --> 01:06:42,611
我们最好的侦探专家 有时也难免被人甩了
Even the best of us are thrown off sometimes.

1090
01:06:48,168 --> 01:06:50,470
-什么事? -夏洛克 福尔摩斯?
Yes?

1091
01:06:50,507 --> 01:06:53,341
-怎么了? -你是夏洛克・福尔摩斯先生?
Sherlock Holmes?

1092
01:06:51,062 --> 01:06:51,677
What is it?

1093
01:06:51,791 --> 01:06:53,901
Are you Mr. Sherlock Holmes?

1094
01:06:53,379 --> 01:06:55,606
不 但是我可以代表他
No but I'm acting for him.

1095
01:06:55,890 --> 01:06:58,427
我是为这个到这里来
I've come about this right here.

1096
01:06:59,765 --> 01:07:01,987
要是你有什么事 你可以和我说
If you have any information

1097
01:07:02,751 --> 01:07:07,231
-这个酬金... -是关于汽艇"曙光"号的吗?
you may give to me.

1098
01:07:03,444 --> 01:07:04,758
There's a reward.

1099
01:07:04,870 --> 01:07:07,786
Is it about the steam launch, Aurora?

1100
01:07:07,269 --> 01:07:09,246
我只跟夏洛克・福尔摩斯先生说
I'm telling no one but Mr. Sherlock Holmes.

1101
01:07:09,283 --> 01:07:11,421
别走 进来
No, no; come inside.

1102
01:07:14,308 --> 01:07:16,728
我是个警官
I'm a police officer.

1103
01:07:17,404 --> 01:07:18,579
你看上去就像
You look like one.

1104
01:07:18,617 --> 01:07:20,045
我们会补偿你的
No you will be recompensated

1105
01:07:20,082 --> 01:07:21,194
作为你时间的损失
for your loss of time.

1106
01:07:21,231 --> 01:07:23,155
不会等太久的 坐下
You will not have long to wait.

1107
01:07:23,652 --> 01:07:25,939
Sit down.

1108
01:07:25,323 --> 01:07:26,931
要雪茄吗 Jones先生?
Cigar Mr. Jones?

1109
01:07:26,968 --> 01:07:28,481
谢谢
Oh, thank you for you very much.

1110
01:07:35,493 --> 01:07:36,935
我说 医生
As I was saying Doctor,

1111
01:07:36,972 --> 01:07:38,695
我认为你的朋友
I consider your friend

1112
01:07:38,731 --> 01:07:41,971
夏洛克・福尔摩斯先生 是一个不会被打败的人
Mr. Sherlock Holmes is a man not to be beat.

1113
01:07:42,342 --> 01:07:45,006
他本可以成为最有前途的警官
He would have made

1114
01:07:45,045 --> 01:07:46,820
这话我可以当着任何人讲
the most promising police officer.

1115
01:07:46,856 --> 01:07:49,653
只要稍微循规蹈矩一点
I don't care who knows it.

1116
01:07:47,270 --> 01:07:49,938
With a little more discipline

1117
01:07:49,690 --> 01:07:51,885
别死抱着理论不放
and a lot less theory.

1118
01:07:51,923 --> 01:07:53,009
谢谢
Thank you.

1119
01:07:53,046 --> 01:07:55,431
你或许可以给我提供机会
You might offer me one.

1120
01:08:00,519 --> 01:08:03,023
你这坏蛋
Oh, you rogue

1121
01:08:03,061 --> 01:08:05,242
你可以去做演员了
you would have made an actor

1122
01:08:05,279 --> 01:08:06,368
出色的演员
and a rare one.

1123
01:08:06,405 --> 01:08:09,398
咳嗽声惟妙惟肖
You had the proper workhouse cough,

1124
01:08:09,435 --> 01:08:11,123
两条弱不禁风的腿
and those weak legs of yours

1125
01:08:11,161 --> 01:08:12,450
上台表演能挣10英镑了
there worth 1 0 pounds each.

1126
01:08:12,487 --> 01:08:15,100
我能胜任警官的职位 您太过奖了
A police officer, I'm flattered.

1127
01:08:15,139 --> 01:08:17,802
Jones 我要一只警用汽艇
Jones I shall need a police launch

1128
01:08:17,840 --> 01:08:19,320
在威斯敏斯特待命
at the Westminster steps.

1129
01:08:19,357 --> 01:08:20,320
最快的那种
The fastest you have.

1130
01:08:20,358 --> 01:08:22,288
还有两位健壮的警察  你  我
2 stout men, yourself, myself,

1131
01:08:22,326 --> 01:08:24,222
还有华生 都要有武器
Watson all of us armed.

1132
01:08:24,260 --> 01:08:25,092
这容易安排
That is easily arranged.

1133
01:08:25,129 --> 01:08:27,263
我给当地警局打电话
I will telephone the local station.

1134
01:08:37,537 --> 01:08:39,217
到伦敦塔的时候
When we get to the tower

1135
01:08:39,253 --> 01:08:41,963
把船停在Jacobson船坞的对面
we'll stop opposite of Jacobson's Yard.

1136
01:08:53,845 --> 01:08:55,576
你是怎么找到"曙光"号的?
How did you find the Aurora then?

1137
01:08:55,613 --> 01:08:58,168
我有理由相信汽艇就在不远处
Well I have reasons that the launch couldn't be

1138
01:08:58,205 --> 01:08:59,353
虽然我们看不见它
far often despite of its invisibility.

1139
01:08:59,391 --> 01:09:02,363
所以 先生们 它会在哪里?
So gentlemen, where could it be?

1140
01:09:03,005 --> 01:09:05,248
我猜肯定不在水上
Well out of the water I suppose.

1141
01:09:05,284 --> 01:09:07,231
在船坞里小做修整
In a repair or boat builders yard.

1142
01:09:07,268 --> 01:09:09,005
非常正确
Exactly.

1143
01:09:30,641 --> 01:09:32,718
一个孩子正在那里等着
One of my boys is waiting by the yard

1144
01:09:32,754 --> 01:09:34,084
他会给我们信号
to give us the signal.

1145
01:09:34,122 --> 01:09:36,275
你的计划非常周密 福尔摩斯先生
You planned it all very neatly Mr. Holmes

1146
01:09:36,312 --> 01:09:38,944
不过要由我处理这件事
but if the affair were in my hands

1147
01:09:38,982 --> 01:09:41,144
我一定派出一对能干的警察
I should have a body of police in the yard

1148
01:09:41,181 --> 01:09:43,077
等他们来了把他们都逮捕了
and arrested them when they came down.

1149
01:09:43,115 --> 01:09:44,496
那绝不可能
Which would have been never.

1150
01:09:44,534 --> 01:09:48,065
那个叫Small的人很精明
This man Small is a pretty shrewd fellow.

1151
01:09:48,507 --> 01:09:49,772
如有可疑情况
Anything suspicious

1152
01:09:49,810 --> 01:09:52,417
他可能会再躲一个星期
and he would lie snug for another week.

1153
01:09:53,976 --> 01:09:55,067
先生?
Sir?

1154
01:09:55,104 --> 01:09:57,111
我们已经到了Jacobson船坞的对面
We're opposite Jacobson's Yard now,

1155
01:09:57,149 --> 01:09:58,831
要靠近一些吗
shall we move downstream a little.

1156
01:09:58,868 --> 01:10:02,724
不用 雾气会掩护我们
No this mist may be of an advantage to us.

1157
01:10:02,761 --> 01:10:05,579
我们下去等着
We must lie low and wait.

1158
01:10:33,829 --> 01:10:35,051
你的男孩发信号了
Your boy's signaling,

1159
01:10:35,089 --> 01:10:37,233
我看得很清楚
I can see it plainly.

1160
01:10:54,636 --> 01:10:56,447
那就是"曙光"号
There's the Aurora

1161
01:10:56,485 --> 01:10:58,482
像艘鬼船
going like the devil

1162
01:10:58,659 --> 01:11:00,308
她太快了
She's very fast.

1163
01:11:00,345 --> 01:11:01,813
我猜我们追不上她
I doubt if we shall catch her.

1164
01:11:01,850 --> 01:11:03,421
我们必须追上她!
We must catch her!

1165
01:11:03,459 --> 01:11:05,481
火夫 赶紧加煤!
Pile it on, stokers!

1166
01:11:06,013 --> 01:11:07,288
要是我们追不上她
I'll never forgive myself

1167
01:11:07,325 --> 01:11:09,454
我永远不能原谅自己
if she proves to have some use.

1168
01:11:15,270 --> 01:11:17,071
再快点 再快点
Faster, faster.

1169
01:11:17,071 --> 01:11:19,746
这已经是我们的极限了
This is the fast boat they've got.

1170
01:11:47,091 --> 01:11:49,402
快加煤 火夫!
Pile on the coals.

1171
01:11:50,103 --> 01:11:52,045
一定要追上
Stoke her.

1172
01:11:52,083 --> 01:11:53,920
就算把船烧了
We must have her.

1173
01:11:52,802 --> 01:11:54,912
Even if we burn the boat.

1174
01:12:26,815 --> 01:12:28,468
灯照别太晃
Keep the light steady.

1175
01:12:28,506 --> 01:12:30,719
我几乎看清他的同伙了
I can almost make out his companion.

1176
01:13:21,677 --> 01:13:23,125
我们快追上了
We're gaining.

1177
01:13:38,855 --> 01:13:40,195
火夫 赶紧加煤!
Pile it on, stoker.

1178
01:13:40,234 --> 01:13:42,458
全速前进
Give it all the steam we've got.

1179
01:13:44,095 --> 01:13:46,448
我们赶上了一些
I think we gained a little.

1180
01:13:47,465 --> 01:13:50,275
我一定以及肯定
I'm sure of it.

1181
01:13:49,706 --> 01:13:51,020
Absolutely.

1182
01:14:02,891 --> 01:14:05,224
把灯向左边照照
Point the light more to the left.

1183
01:14:13,230 --> 01:14:14,971
稳住
Keep it steady.

1184
01:14:54,169 --> 01:14:55,895
那艘船怎么了?
What's happening on that boat?

1185
01:14:59,254 --> 01:15:01,388
他们自己打起来了
They're fighting among themselves.

1186
01:15:01,426 --> 01:15:02,380
Tonga
Tonga,

1187
01:15:02,417 --> 01:15:03,972
Tonga
Tonga.

1188
01:15:08,522 --> 01:15:10,076
那个木腿人
The peg leg.

1189
01:15:10,226 --> 01:15:11,512
停船!
Stop!

1190
01:15:11,926 --> 01:15:13,329
我们是警察!
Police!

1191
01:15:13,684 --> 01:15:15,054
快停下!
Cease you.

1192
01:15:15,505 --> 01:15:18,921
你们下地狱吧!
You can burn in hell

1193
01:15:18,960 --> 01:15:21,557
停下!
Stop!

1194
01:15:21,593 --> 01:15:25,843
四签名
The sign of four

1195
01:15:26,763 --> 01:15:29,357
华生 看
Watson look.

1196
01:15:44,330 --> 01:15:46,922
多可怕的脸
What a face.

1197
01:17:59,078 --> 01:18:00,368
等等
Wait

1198
01:18:02,180 --> 01:18:03,570
等等
Wait.

1199
01:18:04,191 --> 01:18:06,347
等他筋疲力尽了再说
Let him wear himself out.

1200
01:18:57,161 --> 01:18:59,661
Jonathan Small
So Jonathan Small.

1201
01:19:00,886 --> 01:19:02,838
抱歉 事情变成这样
I am sorry it's come to this.

1202
01:19:02,875 --> 01:19:06,053
我也一样
And so am I sir.

1203
01:19:07,296 --> 01:19:09,338
但是我发誓 先生们
But I give you my word gentlemen

1204
01:19:09,884 --> 01:19:12,364
我没有对小Sholto先生下手
I never laid hands on young Mr. Sholto.

1205
01:19:12,403 --> 01:19:14,087
你当然没有
Of course you didn't.

1206
01:19:14,123 --> 01:19:15,883
你那个小朋友杀了他
Your little friends dart killed him

1207
01:19:15,920 --> 01:19:18,243
就在你还在爬绳子的时候
while he was still climbing the rope.

1208
01:19:25,891 --> 01:19:28,530
你说这话就好像你亲眼见过一样
Well you speak as if you were there sir.

1209
01:19:41,346 --> 01:19:44,461
要是那是老Sholto少校的话
Well if it had been old Major Sholto

1210
01:19:44,499 --> 01:19:49,141
我绝对会毫不手软地掐死他
I would have swung for him with a light heart.

1211
01:19:49,636 --> 01:19:52,496
现在竟然因为小Sholto而入狱
But to be lagged over this young Sholto,

1212
01:19:55,127 --> 01:19:56,775
真令人心痛
cursed heart.

1213
01:19:57,172 --> 01:19:59,978
如果你能向我句句属实
You must make a clean breast of it

1214
01:20:00,321 --> 01:20:02,364
我还能帮你的忙
if you do I may be of use to you.

1215
01:20:04,186 --> 01:20:06,567
真像是一家人团圆
Quite a family party.

1216
01:20:07,927 --> 01:20:10,061
我想这瓶酒该留给我自己
I reckon I'll pull that flask myself.

1217
01:20:13,412 --> 01:20:17,539
好了 你准备去哪儿 Small?
Now, where are you going Small?

1218
01:20:18,082 --> 01:20:20,830
Gravesend的Esmeralda
The Esmeralda, at Gravesend,

1219
01:20:20,868 --> 01:20:22,853
转道去巴西
outward bound for the Brazils.

1220
01:20:22,890 --> 01:20:24,323
几乎就成功了
And nearly made it.

1221
01:20:24,362 --> 01:20:26,430
如果当时还有别人驾驶的话
Another man at the engines

1222
01:20:26,467 --> 01:20:28,176
你们永远都追不上我们
and you'd never have caught us.

1223
01:20:30,100 --> 01:20:31,937
钥匙在哪?
Where's the key my man?

1224
01:20:34,015 --> 01:20:36,720
河底
At the bottom of the river.

1225
01:20:38,188 --> 01:20:40,008
瞧
Now look here,

1226
01:20:40,046 --> 01:20:41,842
今天你给我们带来了不少麻烦 Small
we've had enough of you tonight Small.

1227
01:20:41,879 --> 01:20:43,695
把手铐带进来 我警告你
Bring the cuffs in men, I'm warning you.

1228
01:20:43,732 --> 01:20:45,400
没事了 警官
Its alright constable

1229
01:20:45,899 --> 01:20:47,548
不必拿手铐来了
When we leave the stacks.

1230
01:20:47,957 --> 01:20:50,354
我建议我们回贝克街
I suggest that we go back to Baker Street.

1231
01:20:50,391 --> 01:20:52,804
我想Morstan小姐在那
Well I think Miss Morstan should be there.

1232
01:20:52,841 --> 01:20:56,156
这不合乎规矩 福尔摩斯先生
Well that's not the regulation way Mr. Holmes.

1233
01:20:56,193 --> 01:20:59,221
至少我可以请你喝上一杯
Well I can at least promise you a nice,

1234
01:20:59,259 --> 01:21:02,196
温暖又美味
warming drink.

1235
01:21:03,876 --> 01:21:05,548
很好 各位
Very well gentlemen.

1236
01:21:13,252 --> 01:21:14,445
Morstan小姐
Well Miss Morstan

1237
01:21:14,987 --> 01:21:17,094
我很荣幸能将
I am pleased and proud

1238
01:21:17,130 --> 01:21:21,266
这个贼绳之以法
to have been able to bring the thief to justice.

1239
01:21:21,352 --> 01:21:24,270
正义!
Justice?

1240
01:21:24,308 --> 01:21:26,584
多好听的正义啊
The pretty justice.

1241
01:21:26,963 --> 01:21:30,050
这财宝不是我们的 还能属于谁?
Who's loot is this if it is not ours?

1242
01:21:30,088 --> 01:21:33,183
财宝不是他们的 却偏要给他们
Where is the justice that I should give it up

1243
01:21:33,221 --> 01:21:34,170
这就是正义?
to those who have never owned it?

1244
01:21:34,208 --> 01:21:35,123
你忘记了 Small
You forget Small

1245
01:21:35,160 --> 01:21:38,104
他们一无所知
they know nothing of this matter.

1246
01:21:38,562 --> 01:21:39,447
判断不出
We cannot tell how far justice

1247
01:21:39,484 --> 01:21:44,165
正义是否在你一边

1248
01:21:41,179 --> 01:21:45,670
may have originally been on your side.

1249
01:21:49,646 --> 01:21:51,345
对 先生
No sir.

1250
01:21:52,269 --> 01:21:55,577
您说话还算公道
You have been fair spoken to me,

1251
01:21:56,489 --> 01:21:58,043
虽然说我该感谢你
though I can say that it's you

1252
01:21:58,081 --> 01:22:00,768
给我的双手
that I have to thank

1253
01:22:00,806 --> 01:22:04,629
戴上了手铐
for these bracelets on my wrists.

1254
01:22:06,755 --> 01:22:09,633
可我并不怨恨
Still I bear no grudge for that.

1255
01:22:10,449 --> 01:22:11,969
要是您想听我的故事
If you want to hear my story

1256
01:22:12,007 --> 01:22:14,627
我不会隐瞒
I have no wish to hold it back.

1257
01:22:14,665 --> 01:22:16,407
我所说之言
And what I say to you is God's truth,

1258
01:22:16,445 --> 01:22:20,254
句句都是真话

1259
01:22:19,178 --> 01:22:21,293
every word of it.

1260
01:22:39,471 --> 01:22:41,354
当我还是个小伙子
When I was a lad

1261
01:22:41,803 --> 01:22:43,921
参军当了兵
I took the Queen's shilling and was

1262
01:22:43,958 --> 01:22:47,597
跟随步兵三团去了印度
posted out to India with the Third Buff's.

1263
01:22:51,856 --> 01:22:54,110
当我在恒河里游泳的时候
A crocodile snapped this off

1264
01:22:54,147 --> 01:22:56,926
一只鳄鱼咬掉了我的腿
when I was bathing in the Ganges.

1265
01:23:00,639 --> 01:23:05,763
那畜生像做外科手术一样 干脆地咬掉了我这只腿
The sawbones had my stump

1266
01:23:03,524 --> 01:23:06,721
in the tar barrel nice and quick.

1267
01:23:06,134 --> 01:23:08,568
我那时还年盛体强
I was young and strong.

1268
01:23:10,267 --> 01:23:12,263
我奉命退伍
We got my discharge and this fellow...

1269
01:23:12,300 --> 01:23:23,239
而这个家伙....支撑着我

1270
01:23:20,536 --> 01:23:23,661
it's been a good support to me

1271
01:23:25,629 --> 01:23:28,900
于是我20岁就成了瘸子
so there I was a cripple at 20.

1272
01:23:29,657 --> 01:23:31,774
但是我喜欢那里
But I liked it out there

1273
01:23:32,356 --> 01:23:34,578
我在那找了一个监工的工作
so I found myself a job as an overseer

1274
01:23:34,615 --> 01:23:36,900
在一个经营靛青的农场里
on an Indigo farm.

1275
01:23:37,450 --> 01:23:40,967
我每天都骑在马背上 所以境遇还不错
I was on horseback all day so that was fine.

1276
01:23:42,558 --> 01:23:45,364
但是好景不长
But I was never in luck for long,

1277
01:23:45,950 --> 01:23:47,655
事前没有一点征兆
without a note of warning

1278
01:23:47,692 --> 01:23:49,929
大叛乱爆发了
the great mutiny was on us.

1279
01:23:50,460 --> 01:23:52,114
一天晚上我回到农场
I came back to the farm one evening to find

1280
01:23:52,151 --> 01:23:55,531
发现我的雇主和所有的人都被杀了
my master and all his family be murdered.

1281
01:23:56,707 --> 01:23:58,573
我没有等待
I didn't wait.

1282
01:23:58,610 --> 01:24:01,832
连夜跑到Agra城
On that same evening I was in the Fort of Agra,

1283
01:24:01,869 --> 01:24:04,806
那是英国人控制着的最近的城市
the nearest city still held by the British.

1284
01:24:05,659 --> 01:24:07,680
古老的Agra城
The old Fort of Agra,

1285
01:24:07,717 --> 01:24:09,419
一个古怪的地方
a queer place,

1286
01:24:10,108 --> 01:24:11,859
很大
huge,

1287
01:24:12,523 --> 01:24:15,693
到处都是通道和房间
it's full of passages and rooms

1288
01:24:17,654 --> 01:24:20,715
更多的是出口 数也数不过来
and more entrances than you can count.

1289
01:24:21,910 --> 01:24:23,839
有很多的门
There were many gates

1290
01:24:23,877 --> 01:24:25,638
由于我是一个退伍兵  还是英国人
and because I was an ex-soldier and British

1291
01:24:25,675 --> 01:24:27,367
他们让我当了一个头目
they put me in charge of one of them

1292
01:24:27,404 --> 01:24:28,715
还给我派了几个印度人
and gave me a couple of Sikkhs

1293
01:24:28,753 --> 01:24:30,629
他们对我们很忠诚

1294
01:24:31,227 --> 01:24:33,390
这是个偏僻的地方
who'd stayed loyal to us.

1295
01:24:32,247 --> 01:24:34,956
It was a lonely place.

1296
01:24:34,454 --> 01:24:37,726
我手下的两个旁遮普人久经沙场
My 2 Punjabis were experienced, fighting men.

1297
01:24:38,700 --> 01:24:43,291
Kartar Singh和Indigo Singh
Kartar Singh and Indigo Singh.

1298
01:24:54,408 --> 01:24:55,500
是叛军吗?
Rebels?

1299
01:24:55,538 --> 01:24:57,089
不是
No rebels.

1300
01:24:57,127 --> 01:24:59,154
堡垒很安全
The fort is safe.

1301
01:24:59,634 --> 01:25:02,963
河这边没有叛军士兵
There are no rebel this side of the river.

1302
01:25:03,890 --> 01:25:05,923
你要不和我们合作
You must be with us

1303
01:25:05,961 --> 01:25:08,782
要不永远沉默
or you must be silenced forever.

1304
01:25:08,819 --> 01:25:10,411
和你们合作干什么?
With you how?

1305
01:25:10,449 --> 01:25:12,843
我们让你发财
We want you to be rich,

1306
01:25:12,881 --> 01:25:16,011
不就是你们英国人来这的目的吗
which is why you British came to this land.

1307
01:25:17,444 --> 01:25:19,921
我没理由拒绝发财
Well I have no objection of being rich.

1308
01:25:19,958 --> 01:25:23,731
以你父亲的身体发誓
Then swear by the bones of your father

1309
01:25:23,768 --> 01:25:24,917
今后绝不做不利于我们的事
to raise no hand

1310
01:25:24,956 --> 01:25:26,917
也不说不利于我们的话
and to speak no word against us now

1311
01:25:26,954 --> 01:25:30,212
永远都不
or ever afterwards

1312
01:25:30,250 --> 01:25:34,040
你会拥有财宝的四分之一
then you will have quarter of the treasure.

1313
01:25:35,411 --> 01:25:37,304
但我们只有3个人
But there are only 3 of us.

1314
01:25:37,340 --> 01:25:39,962
Jagodish Singh 我的同胞兄弟
Jagodish Singh my foster brother

1315
01:25:40,001 --> 01:25:41,819
他也有一份
he must have his share.

1316
01:25:43,528 --> 01:25:48,780
没时间了 先生 决定吧
There is no time Sahib decide.

1317
01:25:49,561 --> 01:25:50,500
好
Well

1318
01:25:50,537 --> 01:25:53,465
如果没有威胁到堡垒的安全
provided the fort is in no kind of danger

1319
01:25:54,387 --> 01:25:56,171
我发誓
I swear.

1320
01:25:58,104 --> 01:26:01,174
你会怎么做 福尔摩斯先生?
What would you have done Mr. Holmes?

1321
01:26:02,006 --> 01:26:03,113
我非常怀疑
I strongly suspect

1322
01:26:03,151 --> 01:26:05,353
我和你完全一样
I would have done exactly as you did.

1323
01:26:07,134 --> 01:26:09,390
我了解锡克人
Yes I know the Sikkh.

1324
01:26:09,703 --> 01:26:11,955
唬弄不了的人
He's not a man to be trifled with.

1325
01:26:15,552 --> 01:26:17,903
我们那里的一个首长
One of our local Rajahs,

1326
01:26:18,505 --> 01:26:19,752
很有钱
Rich as Croesus of course,

1327
01:26:19,791 --> 01:26:21,885
他投靠了叛军
he'd gone in with the rebels.

1328
01:26:21,922 --> 01:26:25,586
但是 他害怕万一英军再反扑回来
But... He wanted to hedge his bet

1329
01:26:25,623 --> 01:26:29,212
又留了后路
just in case the British came out on top.

1330
01:26:29,249 --> 01:26:32,421
他想出个办法 把财产分成2部分
So he made a plot to get half his treasure

1331
01:26:32,459 --> 01:26:34,806
藏在Agra城里
hidden in the Fort of Agra

1332
01:26:35,764 --> 01:26:37,195
派他手下的人
sending one of his men with it

1333
01:26:37,232 --> 01:26:39,735
乔装成商人的样子
in the guise of a merchant

1334
01:26:39,773 --> 01:26:42,384
请Jagodish Singh
and Jagodish Singh

1335
01:26:42,422 --> 01:26:43,572
就是Kartar的哥哥
Kartar's brother

1336
01:26:43,610 --> 01:26:45,928
来做向导
to be the guide.

1337
01:26:45,965 --> 01:26:49,027
他们冒着风险来
They come challenging sahib, in a major way

1338
01:26:49,065 --> 01:26:50,721
按照惯例问他 别吓着他
giving no caution to fear.

1339
01:26:50,758 --> 01:26:51,451
下一步怎么办?
What then?

1340
01:26:51,488 --> 01:26:53,155
我们都安排好了
we do what has to be done.

1341
01:27:06,166 --> 01:27:07,456
谁?
Who goes there?

1342
01:27:07,493 --> 01:27:10,422
自己人 阁下
A friend sahib.

1343
01:27:10,461 --> 01:27:13,214
先验清楚
A friend advance and be recognized.

1344
01:27:17,373 --> 01:27:19,047
你拿的是什么?
What have you with you?

1345
01:27:19,084 --> 01:27:24,395
一个箱子 先生 旧箱子
A box sahib, old box.

1346
01:27:24,432 --> 01:27:27,228
一些祖传的东西
Having some family papers.

1347
01:27:27,266 --> 01:27:31,533
别人拿着不值钱 自己留着
No good to nobody sahib only for myself.

1348
01:27:41,267 --> 01:27:43,611
长官 我不是讨饭的穷人
Sahib, I'm no ordinary beggar.

1349
01:27:45,666 --> 01:27:47,779
我会报答你的 先生
You will have money sahib.

1350
01:27:47,817 --> 01:27:50,195
还有你的同志们
and you comrades sahib also.

1351
01:27:55,067 --> 01:27:57,615
把他带到总部去
Take him to the main guardroom.

1352
01:28:22,102 --> 01:28:26,223
他就这样被死神紧紧包围着
Never was a man more compassed round with death.

1353
01:29:00,166 --> 01:29:01,562
要是他逃跑
If that man had escaped

1354
01:29:01,600 --> 01:29:03,516
整个事情都会败露
the whole affair would have come out.

1355
01:29:03,552 --> 01:29:05,738
我会被枪决的
I should have been shot most like.

1356
01:29:08,379 --> 01:29:11,328
当时的情况下 你们哪个不会这么做?
Which of you would have held back his musket?

1357
01:29:15,391 --> 01:29:17,253
Kartar要火化他
Kartar was for burning him,

1358
01:29:17,291 --> 01:29:19,043
那是他们的宗教信仰
that's there religion.

1359
01:29:19,422 --> 01:29:21,448
但是点火是不可能的
But such a fire was impossible.

1360
01:29:22,276 --> 01:29:24,395
Jagodish要把他扔进
Jagodish was for throwing him down

1361
01:29:24,432 --> 01:29:25,927
堡垒下的深沟里
into the great ditch below the fort

1362
01:29:25,965 --> 01:29:28,249
下面的柴狗会把他吃干净
where the jackal's to clean him.

1363
01:29:28,994 --> 01:29:30,598
毫无疑问他是对的
No doubt he was right.

1364
01:29:31,414 --> 01:29:34,668
我一向对死亡有些许的敬意
I'm always for showing some respect for the dead.

1365
01:29:35,522 --> 01:29:38,363
接着我们打开箱子
Then we turned to the box,

1366
01:29:39,738 --> 01:29:41,438
这个箱子
this box.

1367
01:29:45,846 --> 01:29:47,641
里面的珍宝
Inside were more gems

1368
01:29:47,679 --> 01:29:50,704
我做梦都想不到
than I could have ever even had dreamed of.

1369
01:29:57,471 --> 01:30:01,074
143颗上等钻石
A 1 43 diamonds of the first order

1370
01:30:01,110 --> 01:30:03,555
其中一颗叫做"大莫卧儿"
including the Great Mogul,

1371
01:30:03,593 --> 01:30:06,623
世界上第二大钻石
the second largest stone in existence.

1372
01:30:06,904 --> 01:30:09,263
97块翡翠
97 emeralds,

1373
01:30:09,301 --> 01:30:12,121
170块红宝石
1 70 rubies,

1374
01:30:12,158 --> 01:30:14,436
40块红玉
40 carbuncles,

1375
01:30:14,473 --> 01:30:16,550
61块玛瑙
61 agates.

1376
01:30:21,218 --> 01:30:23,424
Jagodish是对的
Jagodish was right,

1377
01:30:23,461 --> 01:30:28,721
你们这么把他埋了是错误的
it was a great mistake you made

1378
01:30:26,796 --> 01:30:29,755
burying the body as you did

1379
01:30:29,224 --> 01:30:31,361
你说是吗 华生?
would you not say so Watson?

1380
01:30:32,265 --> 01:30:33,576
确实
Yes indeed.

1381
01:30:33,613 --> 01:30:35,898
尸体在印度没被火化的话
Bodies not burned in India

1382
01:30:35,937 --> 01:30:37,228
不久就会被发现
are soon discovered.

1383
01:30:37,266 --> 01:30:38,982
于是你和你的三个同谋
So you and your 3 companions

1384
01:30:39,019 --> 01:30:42,491
被起诉有罪 被叛终身监禁
were found guilty and sent away for life

1385
01:30:42,528 --> 01:30:45,374
在安达曼群岛
to the penal colony in the Andaman Islands.

1386
01:30:45,834 --> 01:30:47,747
布莱尔岛
Blair Island sir.

1387
01:30:47,785 --> 01:30:50,380
希望之城
Hopetown,

1388
01:30:50,899 --> 01:30:54,217
没有什么地方的名字比那儿更糟了
never was a place worse named.

1389
01:31:08,120 --> 01:31:10,049
那是一个苦力之地
It was a place to sweat.

1390
01:31:10,412 --> 01:31:12,814
一个腐朽之地
A place to rot.

1391
01:31:12,852 --> 01:31:15,420
一个死亡之地
A place to die.

1392
01:31:15,458 --> 01:31:19,132
我在那里年复一年的做劳力
And I sweated there year after year

1393
01:31:19,169 --> 01:31:22,509
直到你父亲的到来  Morstan小姐
until your father arrived Miss. Morstan.

1394
01:31:23,679 --> 01:31:25,317
下士!
corporal!

1395
01:31:25,747 --> 01:31:29,294
你不能虐待白人囚犯
you will not maltreat the white prisoner.

1396
01:31:29,332 --> 01:31:32,658
要是再有一次 你就等着受罚吧
If it happens again

1397
01:31:31,745 --> 01:31:33,729
you'll be court marshaled.

1398
01:31:36,694 --> 01:31:38,465
他是我们的行政长官
He was our administrative officer and he gave me

1399
01:31:38,502 --> 01:31:42,434
他在诊疗所给了我一个简易的小屋
a nice cushy villa in the dispensary.

1400
01:31:43,011 --> 01:31:45,152
他是我曾经遇到的
He was as good and kind a Christian gentleman

1401
01:31:45,189 --> 01:31:47,666
最善良基督信徒了
as I ever come across

1402
01:31:48,189 --> 01:31:50,315
我对他没有半点怨恨
and I hold no grudge against him.

1403
01:31:52,430 --> 01:31:54,328
你也是 小姐
Or you Miss.

1404
01:32:05,495 --> 01:32:08,306
谢谢 Small先生
Thank you Mr. Small.

1405
01:32:18,673 --> 01:32:21,524
我坐在这儿 想那些财宝的时候
Well as I sat thinking about the treasure

1406
01:32:21,562 --> 01:32:25,494
我仿佛看见那所有的长官
I could see all the offices and the prison officials

1407
01:32:25,531 --> 01:32:27,692
喝酒 赌博的场景
at their drinking and their gambling.

1408
01:32:29,763 --> 01:32:32,361
Sholto少校从来运气都不好
Major Sholto never had much luck.

1409
01:32:32,859 --> 01:32:35,695
每晚他都输
Night after night he was the loser.

1410
01:32:37,598 --> 01:32:39,999
有些人天生如此
Some people are born like that.

1411
01:32:40,037 --> 01:32:42,222
我输光了 Morstan
It's all over for me Morstan.

1412
01:32:42,259 --> 01:32:44,129
我完了
I'm ruined.

1413
01:32:44,165 --> 01:32:46,909
我得辞职了
I shall have to send in my paper.

1414
01:32:48,143 --> 01:32:51,649
我想你没法再弄到几百块了?
I don't suppose you could manage

1415
01:32:52,346 --> 01:32:56,076
我有自己的烦恼
another couple of hundred hey?

1416
01:32:53,322 --> 01:32:56,482
I had a pretty nasty face in myself

1417
01:32:56,114 --> 01:32:58,610
我有个女儿要抚养
and I have a daughter back home to support.

1418
01:32:58,647 --> 01:33:03,231
我也有两个儿子要养活
Well I've got 2 wretched sons.

1419
01:33:03,270 --> 01:33:04,586
完蛋了
Ruined hey, damn pity.

1420
01:33:07,308 --> 01:33:13,453
所以你决定要接近你的恩人Morstan上尉?
So you decided to approach your benefactor

1421
01:33:13,490 --> 01:33:15,864
他经常在诊疗所里
Captain Morstan?

1422
01:33:14,205 --> 01:33:16,225
He was often in the dispensary.

1423
01:33:15,902 --> 01:33:18,229
热带的气候不适合他
The tropical climate didn't agree with him.

1424
01:33:18,733 --> 01:33:19,775
他心脏很弱
His heart was weak

1425
01:33:19,811 --> 01:33:21,887
全身血液中毒
and his blood was all poisoned.

1426
01:33:22,043 --> 01:33:27,586
知道他会把他所有的安排 都告诉了他的朋友Sholto少校?
Knowing that he would wish to share

1427
01:33:24,384 --> 01:33:25,915
any arrangement with his friend

1428
01:33:26,023 --> 01:33:28,244
the officer in command, Major Sholto?

1429
01:33:27,623 --> 01:33:30,243
是的 那看上去是最安全的方式
Yes sir it seemed the safest way.

1430
01:33:30,282 --> 01:33:31,995
这是你个人的私事
And is there any private concern over which

1431
01:33:32,032 --> 01:33:37,144
你当然有权按你的方式来处理它们
of course you have the power of disposing

1432
01:33:35,784 --> 01:33:40,513
as you think best

1433
01:33:40,190 --> 01:33:41,657
谢谢你的忠告
Thank you for that advice sir.

1434
01:33:41,694 --> 01:33:43,478
非常感谢
Thank you indeed

1435
01:33:43,936 --> 01:33:45,219
但事实是
but the fact is

1436
01:33:45,256 --> 01:33:47,885
我在这种环境下
being in the position I am

1437
01:33:47,922 --> 01:33:49,586
我需要帮助
I need help.

1438
01:33:50,623 --> 01:33:51,951
哪种帮助
What sort of help?

1439
01:33:53,024 --> 01:33:55,042
我要一个同伴
I need a partner.

1440
01:33:56,781 --> 01:34:01,957
我想Sholto少校和我可以帮助你
Well I'm sure Major Sholto and myself

1441
01:33:59,282 --> 01:34:02,407
would like to help you if we could.

1442
01:34:01,994 --> 01:34:04,371
至少我们可以谈谈
We could at least talk about,

1443
01:34:04,408 --> 01:34:08,222
要是我们同意
that is of course if we can agree as to terms.

1444
01:34:09,481 --> 01:34:12,960
在这样的处境下 我只有一个条件
There's only one bargain

1445
01:34:11,658 --> 01:34:14,723
a man in my position can make.

1446
01:34:13,962 --> 01:34:15,658
恢复我的自由
In exchange for my freedom

1447
01:34:15,696 --> 01:34:18,083
还有我那三个同伴
and that of my 3 companions

1448
01:34:18,121 --> 01:34:21,583
我们会将宝物的五分之一分给你们
we shall give you a fifth share

1449
01:34:21,620 --> 01:34:23,060
五分之一?
to divide between you.

1450
01:34:23,701 --> 01:34:25,442
那可不多啊
A fifth?

1451
01:34:25,480 --> 01:34:28,092
至少五万英镑
That isn't very much.

1452
01:34:25,951 --> 01:34:29,291
50 thousand at the least.

1453
01:34:28,870 --> 01:34:30,788
可我们怎么恢复你们的自由呢?
Anyway how can we possibly

1454
01:34:30,825 --> 01:34:32,604
你要知道 这不可能
give you your freedom?

1455
01:34:32,641 --> 01:34:35,543
我们要的就是一只船和足够的食物
You know it's impossible.

1456
01:34:34,004 --> 01:34:37,129
All we need is a boat and provisions.

1457
01:34:36,146 --> 01:34:38,284
在Calcutta或是Madras
There are plenty little yachts and yawls

1458
01:34:38,322 --> 01:34:41,123
有很多的小快艇
in Calcutta or Madras,

1459
01:34:41,160 --> 01:34:44,314
这些就够了
Well enough to serve our purpose.

1460
01:34:44,352 --> 01:34:46,187
要是你一个人还好办
If only there were just one of you.

1461
01:34:46,225 --> 01:34:47,248
不行
None.

1462
01:34:47,552 --> 01:34:49,987
少一个也不行
None or all.

1463
01:34:50,026 --> 01:34:51,787
我们发过誓
We have sworn it.

1464
01:34:51,824 --> 01:34:54,226
四个人要在一起!
The 4 of us must always act together!

1465
01:34:57,436 --> 01:34:58,717
冷静 Sholto
Calm yourself Sholto.

1466
01:34:58,754 --> 01:35:01,590
冷静 想想看
Calm yourself,

1467
01:35:01,628 --> 01:35:03,303
想想看
think about it man,

1468
01:35:03,341 --> 01:35:06,210
Small是一个守信用的人
think about it.

1469
01:35:04,300 --> 01:35:06,664
Small is a man of his word

1470
01:35:06,248 --> 01:35:09,620
他不辜负朋友
he will not abandon his friends.

1471
01:35:09,657 --> 01:35:14,195
我想我们可以信任他
I think we may very well trust him.

1472
01:35:17,684 --> 01:35:20,591
我们第二天的凌晨见了面
We met the next morning in the small hours.

1473
01:35:20,629 --> 01:35:24,193
我详细写下了我们的协议
I had our written agreement in every detail.

1474
01:35:25,974 --> 01:35:29,483
作为大英维多利亚女王领导下军队的长官...
We being officers in the Army

1475
01:35:29,946 --> 01:35:34,222
作为大英维多利亚女王领导下军队的长官...
of her majesty Queen Victoria...

1476
01:35:30,585 --> 01:35:32,569
We being officers in the Army

1477
01:35:32,678 --> 01:35:34,555
of her majesty Queen Victoria...

1478
01:35:34,261 --> 01:35:36,287
在神圣的圣经面前发誓
Do swear on the Holy Bible

1479
01:35:36,324 --> 01:35:39,293
永远遵守协议
that this agreement will always remain

1480
01:35:39,331 --> 01:35:40,723
永不反悔
sacred and binding to us.

1481
01:35:40,761 --> 01:35:42,963
在神圣的圣经面前发誓
Do swear on the Holy Bible

1482
01:35:43,000 --> 01:35:47,539
永远遵守协议 永不反悔
that this agreement will always remain

1483
01:35:45,157 --> 01:35:48,008
sacred and binding to us.

1484
01:35:47,578 --> 01:35:48,824
我给他们每个人一张地图
I gave each of them a plan

1485
01:35:48,862 --> 01:35:51,295
标出了宝藏的位置
showing the position of the treasure.

1486
01:35:58,866 --> 01:36:01,601
这个把我的记忆带回到那时
Oh that brings back memories.

1487
01:36:02,827 --> 01:36:05,036
Sholto坐船去了印度
Sholto took the next boat to India,

1488
01:36:05,074 --> 01:36:06,773
找到了宝藏
found the treasure

1489
01:36:06,811 --> 01:36:08,746
把宝藏带回了英国?
and took it back with him to England?

1490
01:36:08,783 --> 01:36:09,814
是的
Yes.

1491
01:36:10,212 --> 01:36:11,719
当我们听到消息
When we heard the news

1492
01:36:12,156 --> 01:36:15,045
Morstan上尉和我都很气愤
Captain Morstan was as angry as I was.

1493
01:36:15,342 --> 01:36:16,299
他向我发誓
He swore to me he would go home

1494
01:36:16,337 --> 01:36:19,156
要回去找Sholto算账
and settle the matter with Sholto.

1495
01:36:29,820 --> 01:36:33,153
要是他还活着 他会的
And so he would if he lived

1496
01:36:34,146 --> 01:36:36,748
但是那不可能了
but that was not to be.

1497
01:36:44,800 --> 01:36:46,460
从那天起
From that day,

1498
01:36:46,496 --> 01:36:49,448
我只为报仇而活
I lived only for vengeance.

1499
01:36:52,428 --> 01:36:58,641
日夜不忘
I thought of it by day,

1500
01:36:57,113 --> 01:36:59,477
I nursed it by night

1501
01:36:59,091 --> 01:37:00,999
要找到Sholto
to get to Sholto,

1502
01:37:01,538 --> 01:37:03,712
亲手掐住他的喉咙
put my hands on his throat

1503
01:37:03,751 --> 01:37:06,279
那就是我唯一的想法
that was my one thought.

1504
01:37:07,345 --> 01:37:09,008
幸运的是
As luck would have it,

1505
01:37:09,044 --> 01:37:12,392
岛上的一个居民 被带到了我的医疗所
one of the islanders

1506
01:37:12,430 --> 01:37:14,765
被蛇咬伤 大半条命已经没了
had been brought in to my dispensary,

1507
01:37:13,010 --> 01:37:15,647
more than half dead from a snakebite.

1508
01:37:14,803 --> 01:37:18,025
出于人道 我尽所能帮助他
And in common humanity I did my best for him.

1509
01:37:18,512 --> 01:37:20,796
于是他康复过来
Somehow he pulled through

1510
01:37:20,833 --> 01:37:23,980
变得对我非常忠诚
and became very devoted to me,

1511
01:37:25,669 --> 01:37:27,813
一个有趣的小矮子
a funny little fellow.

1512
01:37:29,121 --> 01:37:31,362
先生们
Well you gentlemen

1513
01:37:31,401 --> 01:37:32,983
你们见过他
caught a glimpse of him yourselves,

1514
01:37:33,021 --> 01:37:34,940
毫无疑问 就在昨晚
no doubt, last night.

1515
01:37:35,604 --> 01:37:39,034
他就是忠诚可靠的小Tonga
He was staunch and true little Tonga.

1516
01:37:39,782 --> 01:37:42,740
没有比他更忠诚的同伴了
No man ever had a more faithful mate.

1517
01:37:45,193 --> 01:37:46,969
他是个渔夫
Being by trade a fisherman

1518
01:37:47,005 --> 01:37:49,834
有一只不错的土著船
he had a goodish size native boat

1519
01:37:49,871 --> 01:37:52,632
他同意和我一起逃走
and he had agreed to try to escape with me.

1520
01:39:04,912 --> 01:39:08,165
10天之后 我们遇见了一只商船
After 1 0 days we were picked up by a trader

1521
01:39:08,202 --> 01:39:11,458
带着一批香客 从马来开往吉达
with a cargo of pilgrims from Malay bound for Gito.

1522
01:39:11,496 --> 01:39:13,480
数月之后
After many months

1523
01:39:13,718 --> 01:39:16,769
我们历经艰险
we worked our way across the world

1524
01:39:16,806 --> 01:39:19,411
回到了伦敦
to London.

1525
01:39:22,272 --> 01:39:24,549
过程很精彩
A remarkable account.

1526
01:39:26,029 --> 01:39:29,312
现在 我想Morstan小姐
And now I think Miss Morstan

1527
01:39:29,350 --> 01:39:32,630
可能想看看这些财宝
might like to see the Great Agra Treasure,

1528
01:39:32,667 --> 01:39:36,240
这将使她成为全英国最有钱的女士之一
which will surely make her

1529
01:39:36,276 --> 01:39:38,253
-华生? -没钥匙
one of the richest young ladies in England.

1530
01:39:38,291 --> 01:39:41,249
我想这跟铁火棍可以
Watson?

1531
01:39:38,281 --> 01:39:39,112
There's no key.

1532
01:39:39,223 --> 01:39:41,968
I'm sure our iron poker will oblige.

1533
01:40:09,519 --> 01:40:11,146
Ha ha ha ha ha ha

1534
01:40:17,030 --> 01:40:19,569
这是你做的 Small?
This is your doing Small.

1535
01:40:19,606 --> 01:40:20,520
是的
Yes.

1536
01:40:20,558 --> 01:40:22,477
我把宝藏都扔掉了
Yes I put the treasure away

1537
01:40:22,514 --> 01:40:25,727
你们永远也得不到
where you shall never lay a hand on it.

1538
01:40:25,764 --> 01:40:28,860
没有人能有权利拥有
No living man or woman has any right to it

1539
01:40:28,899 --> 01:40:32,789
除非是在安达曼兵营里的那三个人 还有我
unless it is the 3 men

1540
01:40:30,924 --> 01:40:35,059
in the Andaman Convict Barracks and myself.

1541
01:40:34,422 --> 01:40:37,132
我知道我没机会拥有了
I know now that I cannot have the use of it,

1542
01:40:37,531 --> 01:40:39,222
没人会有
no more can they.

1543
01:40:39,778 --> 01:40:43,618
我做的这些是为了他们 也是为我
But I have acted all along

1544
01:40:41,940 --> 01:40:44,934
for them as much as for myself.

1545
01:40:44,488 --> 01:40:47,123
我们一直把四签名带在身上
We have the sign of four with us always.

1546
01:40:48,413 --> 01:40:50,330
宝藏哪去了?
Where is it?

1547
01:40:50,762 --> 01:40:52,863
在钥匙所在的地方
Where the key is

1548
01:40:52,901 --> 01:40:55,411
在小Tonga所在的地方
and where little Tonga is.

1549
01:40:57,254 --> 01:40:58,967
我看见你们的汽艇要赶上我们
I saw your launch might catch us

1550
01:40:59,004 --> 01:41:01,845
我看小Tonga倒在一边
and I saw little Tonga go over the side.

1551
01:41:04,666 --> 01:41:07,300
我把财宝放到了一个安全的地方
I put the loot in a safe place.

1552
01:41:07,338 --> 01:41:09,898
你骗我们 Small
You are deceiving us Small if you had wished

1553
01:41:09,936 --> 01:41:12,772
要是你想把财宝扔进泰晤士河
to throw the treasure into the Thames

1554
01:41:12,809 --> 01:41:16,031
把箱子扔进去不是更容易
it would have been easier

1555
01:41:16,069 --> 01:41:17,477
我扔得容易
to have thrown box and all.

1556
01:41:17,514 --> 01:41:19,662
你们捞得也容易
Easier for me to throw

1557
01:41:18,301 --> 01:41:21,747
and easier for you to recover.

1558
01:41:20,714 --> 01:41:23,248
有本事把我抓住的人
A man who's clever enough to hunt me down

1559
01:41:23,286 --> 01:41:25,228
也有本事把箱子
is clever enough to pick up a box

1560
01:41:25,265 --> 01:41:27,212
从河底捞上来
from the bottom of the river.

1561
01:41:31,299 --> 01:41:32,371
我很遗憾
I am sorry.

1562
01:41:32,409 --> 01:41:34,877
我很庆幸财宝没了
I am glad the treasure is lost.

1563
01:41:36,658 --> 01:41:40,764
对于拥有宝藏的人来说 它只是个诅咒
It's been nothing but a curse

1564
01:41:39,497 --> 01:41:42,562
to every man who has owned it.

1565
01:41:41,898 --> 01:41:44,927
不仅是我可怜的父亲
And only death to my poor father.

1566
01:41:44,964 --> 01:41:49,262
还有我和我同伴们苦役的生活
And slavery for life

1567
01:41:47,272 --> 01:41:50,302
to me and my companions.

1568
01:41:49,711 --> 01:41:51,487
我们的前半生都
We spent the first half of my life

1569
01:41:51,524 --> 01:41:54,352
在Andaman修水坝
digging a breakwater in the Andaman's.

1570
01:41:55,806 --> 01:41:57,894
可能我的下半生要在
And I'm likely to spend the other half

1571
01:41:57,932 --> 01:42:00,434
Dartmoor修水渠了
digging ditches on Dartmoor.

1572
01:42:03,175 --> 01:42:05,726
福尔摩斯 责任就是责任
Well Holmes duty is duty

1573
01:42:05,765 --> 01:42:08,718
今天对你已经够通融了
and I've gone rather far in bringing him here.

1574
01:42:08,755 --> 01:42:13,122
我相信只有把这个讲故事的人送进监狱
I shall feel more at ease

1575
01:42:13,160 --> 01:42:14,608
我才能放心
when I have our storyteller here

1576
01:42:14,646 --> 01:42:18,825
我很感谢你们的协助
under lock and key.

1577
01:42:15,406 --> 01:42:20,493
I am obliged to you for your assistance.

1578
01:42:19,917 --> 01:42:22,113
再见 华生医生
Good day to you. Doctor Watson,

1579
01:42:22,151 --> 01:42:23,425
Morstan小姐
Miss Morstan.

1580
01:42:29,819 --> 01:42:31,351
你先走 Small
Awe, after you Small.

1581
01:42:31,833 --> 01:42:35,635
否则你要用木腿打我真是太容易了
you seem a bit handy

1582
01:42:33,882 --> 01:42:36,211
with that wooden leg of yours.

1583
01:43:22,412 --> 01:43:25,314
真是惭愧 福尔摩斯先生
I feel most ashamed that you Mr. Holmes

1584
01:43:25,351 --> 01:43:27,457
还有亲爱的华生医生
and you dear Doctor Watson

1585
01:43:27,495 --> 01:43:28,618
让你们为了我的事
have had to put yourself

1586
01:43:28,655 --> 01:43:30,824
冒了那么多的险
into such peril on my behalf.

1587
01:43:30,862 --> 01:43:32,806
一切都结束了 别这么说
Oh that's all over and forgotten.

1588
01:43:32,843 --> 01:43:36,537
Forrester夫人派他的车夫 来接Morstan小姐了
Mrs. Forrester has sent her carriage for Miss Morstan.

1589
01:43:37,572 --> 01:43:39,225
我不会再给你们添麻烦了 两位
I'll impose on you no longer gentlemen.

1590
01:43:39,262 --> 01:43:40,844
你们一定筋疲力尽了
You must be exhausted.

1591
01:43:40,883 --> 01:43:42,651
我承认这次行动消耗了太多精力
Yes I confess the reaction is already upon me.

1592
01:43:42,688 --> 01:43:45,834
我这一个星期都会软绵绵的
I shall be as limp as a rag for a week.

1593
01:43:45,872 --> 01:43:49,411
我很感谢您洗刷了我父亲的名声
I'm so very grateful to you

1594
01:43:48,069 --> 01:43:50,469
for clearing my father's name.

1595
01:43:51,688 --> 01:43:55,698
也很感激您
I'm so very grateful to you both.

1596
01:44:17,789 --> 01:44:19,505
好像不太公平
Seems so unfair.

1597
01:44:21,255 --> 01:44:23,234
这个案子里都是你在做事
You ve done all the work in this business

1598
01:44:23,678 --> 01:44:26,296
Athelney Jones却赢得了名声
and Athelney Jones gets all the credit.

1599
01:44:29,706 --> 01:44:31,415
你得到了什么?
What remains for you?

1600
01:44:32,995 --> 01:44:35,823
对于我 我得到了解决 一件有趣案子的快乐
For me, the pleasure of having solved

1601
01:44:35,861 --> 01:44:37,752
几乎是独自一人完成的
an interesting case almost single-handed.

1602
01:44:38,992 --> 01:44:40,274
对于你 毫无疑问
And for you no doubt the pleasure

1603
01:44:40,311 --> 01:44:43,976
得到了把故事写下来的快乐

1604
01:44:44,014 --> 01:44:49,588
以你那种通俗的浪漫的形式
of writing it up

1605
01:44:44,756 --> 01:44:49,938
in your usual flowery and romantic style.

1606
01:45:27,178 --> 01:45:30,554
多迷人的女人
What a very attractive woman.

1607
01:45:32,221 --> 01:45:34,234
她吗?
Was she?

1608
01:45:34,877 --> 01:45:37,169
我没注意
I hadn't noticed.

1609
